title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Mix cocoa and soda and add boiling water.
Add flour and buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Then add cocoa mixture and vanilla.
Bake in slow oven at 350°.

title: pecan coffee cake
directions: Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender. Add remaining ingredients and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Add topping and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, butter, shortening, vanilla and baking powder together.
Stir in flour until stiff.
Turn out on floured board and knead, then roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: triple chocolate kahlua cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 375°.
Cool 20 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Very moist cake!

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs; add other ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet, 2 tablespoons for each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mocha fudge cake(don't be alarmed that there is no flour in this cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Butter a round 9 x 3-inch cake pan with a removable bottom and line with 1 piece of foil, pushing the foil onto the bottom, up the sides and over the rim smoothly and without tearing.
(Foil which is 12 inches wide can be used, but you will then need 2 pieces.
Overlap them and fold them together as smoothly as possible.
You do not want the batter to leak through.) Lightly but thoroughly butter the foil.

title: fresh vegetable marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour over fresh vegetables and marinate overnight.

title: linda reneau's toasted coconut pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, sugar, butter, lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir in coconut and pecans, then pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fabulous shortbread cookies
directions: Work cold butter with hands until soft and creamy, but not too soft.
Add sugar and mix.
In another bowl, mix together the flour and salt. Mix this into the butter-sugar mixture with your fingers until the particles cling together.

Gather the dough into a ball, kneading gently until it becomes smooth and soft, not too oily. Try not to handle the dough too much. The warmth from the hands melts the butter even more and over-develops the butter.
Pat the dough into a rectangle, 3/8-inch thick.
Mark out the pieces with fork tines.
Use a dull knife to score the dough into small 1 1/2 x 2-inch rectangular pieces.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours. Remove the pan from the refrigerator and deepen the slice lines to remove from the pan.
Bake pieces on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Add cut-up shrimp to softened cream cheese.
Blend in seasonings.
Mix well and work into balls with hands.
You can either roll in pecans or sprinkle red pepper or Creole seasoning.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Melt butterscotch bits in top of double boiler over hot water. When melted, pour over nuts and noodles.
Drop by little teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Yields 30 to 40.

title: german pound cake
directions: All ingredients must be room temperature.
In a large bowl, cream butter; sift sugar.
Add gradually to butter.
Add unbeaten egg yolks one at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Mix extracts, sift flour with baking powder.
Add salt.
Starting and ending with flour, alternate with milk to creamed mixture.
Beat egg white until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Grease a 12-cup Bundt pan.
Place 24 almonds on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with a teaspoon of sugar for darker crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: low-fat fudgy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat an 8-inch square baking dish with vegetable cooking spray.
Cut chocolate into 1-inch pieces and place in a heatproof bowl.
Set over low heat in a small skillet containing 1/2 inch simmering water.
Stir occasionally just until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat; set aside.
In a mixer bowl, combine all ingredients except flour and walnuts; beat to blend thoroughly.
Mix in flour.
Spread batter in prepared pan; sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake about 30 minutes until springy to the touch around edges.
Cool on rack; cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in well-greased tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: ground beef and sausage snack
directions: Crumble meat and cook until brown.
Drain fat, then put in cheese (cut up or grated) and toss together until cheese melts. Place spoonful or so on round pieces of bread and put bread on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, remove from cookie sheet and put into plastic bags to store in freezer.

title: chocolate cheesecake cupcakes(serves 18)
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, egg and sugar.
Stir in chocolate chips and set aside.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Melt butter; saute onion and brown meat and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer 20 minutes.
Soften cream cheese; beat with mixer.
Add sour cream.
Cook spaghetti.
Coat 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Layer as follows: cooked spaghetti, cheese mixture and meat mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla, salt, Pet milk and cornstarch. Pour into gallon freezer.
Fill remainder of freezer with whole milk.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, dill, salt and pepper. Add elbow macaroni, cucumber, tomatoes and onions.
Toss to coat well.

title: ellen's barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine the meat, milk, oatmeal, cracker crumbs, eggs, onion (1/2 cup), garlic powder, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Mix will be soft.
Shape into walnut-size balls.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: chicken delight
directions: Season chicken breasts with garlic salt, pepper and Creole seasoning.
Saute chicken in skillet with a small amount of oil. Remove chicken and add the vegetables.
Saute vegetables, then add the Ro-Tel and spaghetti sauce to the vegetables.
Stir, then add the chicken.
Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with spaghetti or rice.

title: sandra's super moist coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Bake in 2 round 9-inch pans. Cool cake 15 minutes. Poke holes down through cake with a fork. In a saucepan, combine milk, sugar and 1/2 cup coconut. Bring to a boil.

Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute. Mixture will be runny. Carefully spoon over warm cake, allowing liquid to soak down through holes. Do them layer by layer. After you have finished the 1st layer, let it cool. Fold 1/2 cup coconut in Cool Whip and spread over 1st layer. Place 2nd layer on top of 1st and repeat with spooning the liquid, allowing it to soak down through holes. You do not have to use all of the liquid. Next, top with Cool Whip mixture. Sprinkle remaining coconut on cake. Chill. Store in refrigerator.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Pour melted butter in baking dish.
Pour half of stuffing mix over butter.
Layer chicken over stuffing.
Pour on soup.
Put rest of stuffing over soup.
Pour chicken broth evenly over all of it.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream butter (Crisco) and sugar.
Add eggs, then crushed pineapple.
Add dry ingredients. Drop from spoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: brisket to brag about
directions: Press pepper into meat.
Mix other ingredients and pour over meat.
Marinate overnight.
Wrap meat and liquid tightly in heavy foil for baking.
Bake for 3 hours in 350° oven.
Sprinkle with fajita seasoning as baking or bake half the time and finish on grill.

title: friendship cake
directions: Stir every day; use wooden spoon.

title: chocolate chunk brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine margarine, sugar, eggs, cocoa and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine flour and baking powder.
Stir both mixtures together, then add in pecans and chocolate chunks.
Spread batter into a lightly greased 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out barely moist.
Let cool in pan.
Cut into squares and sprinkle confectioners sugar on top, if desired.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Saute chicken in butter.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Add carrots and thawed broccoli, soup, water and rice.
Cover and cook until rice is done.
Serves 4.

title: linguini with red clam sauce
directions: Cut up onion, green pepper and celery.
Saute vegetables in oil and garlic until tender.
Add tomatoes (drain liquid).
Add bay leaf.
Add clam sauce (include liquid).
Simmer for 1/2 hour until sauce thickens.
Stir constantly.
Cook linguini and serve sauce over pasta.

title: original ranch house chili
directions: Brown ground chuck, ground beef and pork in 1 tablespoon oil in a frying pan; drain and set aside.
In 5 quart kettle add 2 tablespoons oil, at medium/high heat stir and add celery, peppers, onion and tomatillas.
Heat and stir until onions are transparent. Add meat to kettle; mix well.
While stirring add water, beer, tomato paste, tomatoes and tomato juice.
Add spices, mix well and turn down to simmer.
Add kidney beans 30 minutes before serving; stir well.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients until blended.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Press into 1 3/4-inch muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Remove from oven and immediately press 1 peanut butter cup candy into each hot cookie crust.
Allow to cool.
Remove from pan.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Melt butter in a frying pan and add onions and garlic. Fry gently until onions begin to brown. Add sausage meat and fry gently for 5 minutes. In a bowl, mix together bulgur, parsley and tomatoes. Add sausage meat mixture; season with salt and pepper. Preheat oven to 375°. Halve bell peppers and discard seeds. Fill peppers with stuffing and place in a shallow baking dish. Drizzle with a little olive oil and bake for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Spread about 3 1/2 quarts of filling in each of 2 large 16 x 24-inch greased sheet pans.

title: curried turkey balls
directions: Soften the cream cheese and mix with the rest of ingredients except coconut.
Form into small balls and roll in coconut.
Makes 40 to 50 balls.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Make one day ahead.
Let soften.
Refrigerate overnight; will taste better.

title: jordan marsh blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter, sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Sift dry ingredients together, and add alternately with milk. Mix well. Fold in blueberries. Spoon in greased and floured muffin pan. Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° for 30-35 min.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time and beat well after each.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together salt, soda and flour.
Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture, beating well.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 (8 or 9-inch) cake layer pans. Line on bottoms with paper.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Fill layers and frost top and sides with Coconut-Pecan Filling.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: cucumber, onion and pepper salad
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar, water, Mrs. Dash and mustard seed for 2 or 3 minutes.
Let cool, then pour over vegetables.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat; add onion or onion powder and cook.
Add salt and pepper, soup and water.
Stir to heat thoroughly.
Serve with rice, potatoes or noodles.

title: original chex party mix
directions: For hot and spicy, replace 2 tablespoons of Worcestershire sauce with 2 tablespoons Tabasco.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix pretzels, margarine and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool.
Cream the softened cream cheese and 1 cup confectioners sugar.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on pretzel layer. Combine Jell-O and boiling water.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
Allow to cool.
Pour over cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip layer.
Refrigerate until top layer is congealed.
Can be used as a dessert.

title: ham asparagus rolls
directions: Melt butter. Blend in flour and salt. add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thick. Add Swiss cheese and stir until melted. Blend 1 cup sauce with cooked rice. Spoon an equal amount of rice mixture onto narrow end of ham slice.
Top each slice with 3 to 4 asparagus spears. Roll ham around filling.
Arrange in shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over rolls. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a large Pyrex casserole.
(Good for guests, too.)

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Layer ham and then cheese on top.
Melt oleo; sprinkle on top of crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix all together except bacon.
Place in 3-quart casserole dish and dot with crumbled bacon and slices olives if desired. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: amish dressing
directions: Put eggs in bowl and beat.
Add salt, pepper, sage and thyme; mix.
Add 2 cups milk, onion, celery, potatoes, chicken and carrots.
Add bread and enough milk to moisten well.
Substitute 1 cup chicken broth instead of milk to give a good flavor.
Bake in a well-greased casserole at 350°.

title: yogurt-praline candy
directions: Coat wax paper with cooking spray; set aside.
Combine sugars and yogurt in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
(Do not stir.)
Boil 2 to 3 minutes or until a candy thermometer reads 232°.
Remove from heat; stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spoon mixture evenly onto prepared wax paper; let stand until firm.
Break into small pieces.
Store in an airtight container.
Yield:
1 1/2 pounds.

title: pizza dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan. Spread with chili sauce.
Sprinkle with Canadian bacon, onion, green pepper and cheeses.
Serve with chips.
Yield:
14 to 16 servings.

title: sour cream pork chops
directions: Place fried pork chops in casserole dish (may place pasta in first or save these for "on the side").
Cover with soup mixture, chicken soup, onion, sour cream and drippings mixed well.
Layer with more chips, then more soup mixture.
Bake at 350° until onions are done.

title: beef roast on the grill
directions: Warm up sauce.
Marinate meat in sauce for at least 4 hours. Cook on Weber grill, placing roast on grill directly over drip pan.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes per pound.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread pans. Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: tuna-nuna-delight
directions: Boil noodles.
Open cans.
Mix in big dish.
Add bacon and cheese.
Heat for 15 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Um, it is good eatin'!!

title: chewy brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cocoa, sugar and salt.
Mix well. Add eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Pinch pieces of biscuits off and put in a Bundt pan.
Mix oleo, brown sugar, vanilla and cinnamon; pour over each layer of biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg yolks.
Add flour and whiskey alternately, then add cream of tartar and nutmeg.
Beat egg whites well and fold into mixture.
Last, add chopped fruit and nuts which have been dredged with a little flour.
Bake at 225° for 3 or 4 hours, depending on size of cake.
This will make two 6 or 7-pound cakes.
It is very good if you can afford it.

title: italian tortellini soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Add salt and pepper. Bring to a boil over medium heat; reduce heat and simmer until pasta and vegetables are tender, about 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: quick vichyssoise(potato soup)
directions: Combine water, parsley and bouillon in a saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil; stir until bouillon dissolves.
Remove from heat; add cream and stir in potatoes.
Cool at room temperature, 15 minutes.
Transfer to blender container.
Add cream cheese; blend until smooth and chill well.
Serve in chilled cups or bowls. Sprinkle with chives.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Pare and cut potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes.
Boil in salted water until just barely tender, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain thoroughly and toss with butter or margarine and salt and pepper to taste.
Add sour cream, cottage cheese and onions and toss gently until well combined.
Turn mixture into 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and paprika if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly and browned on top.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Place biscuits in bottom of pan and cover with water.
Soak about 30 minutes.
Mix other ingredients and pour over biscuits and water.
Place in 250° oven and bake until golden brown.

title: biscuit mix(bisquick substitute)
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, and dry milk.
Add oleo and cut in with pastry blender until mixture resembles finely-ground meal.
Store in covered container.

title: avocado and cream cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix thoroughly and spread on Honey Wheat Bread.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix the butter or oleo, brown sugar and syrup and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and baking powder.
Put hulless corn in 2 large pans or 1 large deep roaster.
Pour syrup over all evenly and mix well.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Rinse frozen peas under hot water and drain.
Mix all ingredients together with mayo or salad dressing.

title: cheese noodle casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender. Blend in soup.
Gradually stir in milk.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine sauce and cooked macaroni. Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Place cranberries in food processor and finely chop.
Place cored and quartered apples in food processor and finely chop. Quarter oranges (unpeeled) and finely chop.
Use only juice from oranges and about 1/4 cup of chopped orange.
Mix all ingredients in glass bowl and refrigerate overnight to enhance flavor.

title: grandma kline's coffee cake
directions: Dissolve cake yeast in warm water and 1 tablespoon sugar. Cover; let rise.
Add to milk that has been scalded and cooled. Add 2 cups flour; let rise.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour to make soft dough.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let rise.
Put in greased cake pans.
Let rise.
Grandma always kinda pinched her finger 6 or 7 times on top and put mixture of melted butter, brown sugar, cinnamon and cream.
Bake.

title: luscious bars
directions: Mix Karo and sugar and bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter and pour over cereal in a large bowl and mix well.
Press Mixture into a 9x13 greased pan.
Pour morsels which have been melted over hot water or in microwave oven over top.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: myrtle's cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, cinnamon and soda.
Fold in pineapple plus juice.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli until done.
Mix other ingredients together with broccoli.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle with Ritz or Club cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Soak bread crumbs and milk in large bowl for 5 minutes. Meanwhile, in large skillet, saute onion in butter until straw colored, 2 minutes.
Add egg, meats, nutmeg, salt, pepper and onion to bread crumbs.
Mix well with fork.
Shape into 18 meat balls. Heat remaining butter in skillet, brown meat balls well on all sides (10 minutes), a few at a time; remove.
Blend flour into butter in skillet.
Gradually stir in consomme.
Add meat balls; simmer, covered, 10 minutes or until done.
Stir in cream.
Garnish with fresh dill.
Serves 6.

title: white christmas drink
directions: Put all ingredients in a bottle or jar.
Shake well.
Put in fridge for about 4 hours.
When serving, fill one shot glass with mix and add to glass with cream soda.
For extra kick, put in one straight shot of vodka or gin.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Shell and drain shrimp. Place shells in water to make stock. Put shrimp aside. In a large skillet, brown butter. Add flour and stir to make paste. Brown onions, green pepper and garlic in skillet with paste. Drain stock from shells and add 2 cups of stock to skillet along with tomato paste. Cook for 1 hour or until thick. Add shrimp, parsley, scallions, salt and pepper. Cook until shrimp are pink. Serve over rice.

title: feeder lemonade
directions: Add ice and stir.
Garnish with lemon slices and cherries.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in jar.
Spoon 2 heaping teaspoonfuls into 1 cup of hot water.
Sit back and enjoy.

title: no weep meringue
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons sugar, water and cornstarch; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Set aside to cool.

title: cranberry apple casserole
directions: Pile into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Put on topping.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in enough water to allow the beans to swell.
When ready to cook, add 1/2 teaspoon of soda to same water and allow to come to boil.
Drain this water off and cover with fresh water.
Add bacon; cook until beans mash easily against side of dish.
Keeping covered with water, add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or 325° for a longer time.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown turkey.
Add vegetables with juices; cook until vegetables are tender.
Can be made in crock-pot or slow cooker.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and put in casserole dish; top with Pepperidge Farm dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Fry sausage and hamburger; drain.
Add soup to meat (do not add water).
Roll out dough.
Spread meat mixture onto dough. Roll up.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: asparagus shrimp salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Arrange asparagus on serving plate.
Spoon shrimp salad over asparagus.
Garnish with lemon wedges. Serve chilled.
Serves 4.

title: yams with peaches
directions: Place peach halves, cut side up, on glass serving platter. Combine 4 tablespoons peach syrup and remaining ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into peach halves. Microwave on Reheat for 6 to 7 minutes or until hot. Let stand for 3 minutes before serving.

title: eggplant
directions: Put slices of cheese between 2 slices of eggplant.
Dip in egg, then seasoned bread crumbs.
Fry in oil on both sides.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract; beat until creamy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in Nestle semi-sweet real chocolate morsels.
Spread evenly into well greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven* and cool completely.
Cut into 2 inch squares.
Makes 35 (2 inch) squares.

title: easy crab imperial
directions: Remove all
cartilage
from crab meat.	In medium-sized pan, melt 1 tablespoon butter.
Mix in flour, slowly add milk, stirring constantly to
keep
free
of
lumps.
Cook, stirring over medium heat
until
mixture comes to a boil and thickens. Mix in onions, Worcestershire
sauce
and bread cubes.
Cool. Fold in mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In another pan, heat 2 tablespoons
butter
until	lightly browned.
Add crabmeat and toss
lightly.
Combine
with sauce mixture.
Put mixture in individual	shells	or
greased
1	quart casserole dish. Sprinkle paprika
over top.
Bake at 450° until hot and bubbly and lightly browned
on top, 10 to 15 minutes.	Makes 4 generous servings.

title: chicken fit for a king
directions: Soak dried beef in boiling water for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain. Place in bottom of baking dish.
Wrap each chicken breast with bacon.
Place on top of beef.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup with 1/2 cup water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours. Serve over cooked rice.
Do not add salt.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Drain and save juices from blueberries and pineapple.

title: caramel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to directions on package.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Pour 2/3 of cake batter into pan.
Bake for about 20 minutes, until batter starts to get firm.
While batter is baking, unwrap caramels and place in a double boiler.
Add margarine and melt. When melted and smooth, stir in milk.
Remove cake from oven. Pour caramel mixture over cake.
Spoon remaining 1/3 batter over caramel mixture.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until cake is fully cooked.
Let cool completely.
Cover with chocolate icing and top with nuts.

title: border patrol casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Dump ham, beans and salsa into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Smother with the chips and cheese. Bake for 30 minutes, until cheese melts and the casserole is heated through.

title: microwave chicken parmesan
directions: Mix tomato sauce, Italian seasoning and garlic salt in a 2-cup measure.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High (100%) 2 minutes; stir.
Reduce power to Medium (50%).
Microwave 5 minutes, stirring once; set aside.
Mix corn flake crumbs, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and the parsley flakes.
Dip chicken breasts in eggs, then in crumb mixture.
Place in rectangular baking dish, 8 x 12-inch or 10-inch square casserole.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave at Medium-High (70%) until chicken is tender, 9 to 14 minutes, rearranging after half the cooking time (do not turn over).
Pour sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over chicken breasts.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Microwave at Medium-high (70%) until Mozzarella melts and sauce is hot, 2 to 5 1/2 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate noodles
directions: Add butterscotch candy oil to white chocolate and stir in noodles until thick.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: bread pudding with brandy sauce
directions: Slice
bread
in
1/2-inch wide strips.
In large bowl, mix eggs,
sugar,
salt,
cinnamon, vanilla, butter, milk and applesauce.
Place bread strips in lattice pattern in 11 x 7 x 2-inch
dish.
Top	with
milk mixture.
If milk mixture seems too much,
mash
the bread a little until it absorbs the milk. Bake at 325°
for	1
hour
or
until center is set and bread slightly brown.
Cook thoroughly.
Top with the following.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Cover with water.
Cook until done. Add 2 cups milk and butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy in large mixer bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes; cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute.
Remove to wire rack.

title: scalloped corn and shrimp
directions: In a bowl, combine the corn, onion and salt and pepper.
In a buttered shallow baking dish, sprinkle about 1/4 cup of the cracker crumbs in an even layer; dot them with butter and add half the corn mixture.
Add another 1/4 cup of the crumbs and the remaining corn mixture.
In a saucepan, melt the remaining 3 tablespoons butter; mix in remaining crumbs and sprinkle on top of corn.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: buttermilk pecan chicken fingers
directions: Cut each chicken breast in 3 or 4 strips.
Combine next 6 ingredients and set aside.
Combine egg and buttermilk.
Dip chicken into buttermilk mixture and dredge into flour mixture.
(It works well, good to put flour mixture in a Ziploc bag.)
Pour butter into jelly roll pan.
Add chicken, turning to coat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 24.

title: jewish sour cream coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour coat a 10-inch tube pan. In a large bowl, cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add the sour cream to flour mix and stir well.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: In the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, crumble 2 slices of bread.
Cook and drain sausage or bacon; beat eggs and add milk, salt and pepper.
Put cooked, drained sausage or bacon over bread crumbs.
Pour egg mixture over; cover with grated cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.

title: toffee delight coffee cake
directions: Set aside brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, mix other ingredients. Beat well for 2 minutes.
Pour 1/3 batter in pan.
Sprinkle with half of sugar mixture.
Pour remaining batter and sprinkle remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: imperial cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and flavoring together by hand.
Add flour.
Mix well until you have a soft dough.
Roll out into balls.
Press down with sugared fork.
Bake at 350° to 375° about 12 minutes or until very lightly browned.

title: homemade baby wipes
directions: Cut the roll of paper towels in half so you have 2 rolls about the size of a toilet paper roll.
Mix ingredients together and put into a round container large enough to hold a half roll of paper towels.
Let towels soak and then remove cardboard tube from center.
To use wipes, pull the towels from the center.

title: e-z cobbler
directions: Mix cake as directed and pour in oblong baking pan. Pour fruit on top of mix-in the center. Bake as directed on cake box and serve with ice cream or cool whip.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Break 2 slices of bread into small pieces and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix chicken, pimento, celery, mayonnaise and onion together well and place over bread. Remove crusts from 3 slices of bread and dice; spread over mixture.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over mixture.
Add undiluted mushroom soup to top of casserole.
Spread with grated cheese.
Place almonds on top if desired.
Place in refrigerator over night.
Next day, set it out to get room temperature.
Bake one hour (no longer) at 325°.
Serves 6.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add water, taco seasoning and tomato sauce.
Mix and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in macaroni, chillies and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: zesty lemon curd
directions: In top of a double boiler, combine all ingredients; cook and stir over boiling water until thick like pudding.
Chill until ready to serve.
Spread on muffins, rolls, waffles or ice cream. Keeps well in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
Yields 2 cups.

title: spicy party pecans
directions: In medium bowl, combine whites and water.
Add nuts.
Mix well.
In small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle sugar mixture over nuts.
Mix until well coated.
Spread on a baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Put stew beef in bottom of a roaster or Dutch oven.
Add desired vegetables.
Add tapioca, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour V-8 juice in.
Cover and bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Do not uncover until time is up.

title: lima bean - broccoli casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Mix vegetables, soups and sour cream together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix margarine and Rice Krispies.
Spread over casserole and continue baking 10 to 15 minutes longer, until golden brown.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Mix egg white,	cornstarch,
soy sauce, ginger and salt and pour over chicken pieces.
Let stand for 15 minutes. Brown chicken pieces in hot oil in wok or large frying pan.
Remove. Stir-fry green onions, pea
pods
and
water
chestnuts.
Add chicken pieces and thicken with 1/2 cup water and 1 tablespoon cornstarch. Add cashews and serve immediately over hot steamed rice.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in the work bowl of a food processor.
Add cream cheese in small amounts and blend. Refrigerate for 20 minutes.
To serve, cut bread into shapes. Spread a thin layer of sauce on bread; top with slice of cucumber and dill.

title: easy marinated chicken(microwave)
directions: Marinate chicken about two hours in Ranch dressing.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes, turning at 4 minutes.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Cover and chill in refrigerator overnight.
Form into a ball.
Put 2 tablespoons finely minced parsley and 1/2 cup chopped nuts on a sheet of wax paper.
Roll ball until it is completely covered.
Keep refrigerated.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Combine 4 cups each water and apple juice in a saucepan.
Add 1 cup Kool-Aid brand presweetened soft drink mix (any red flavor), cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
Serve hot.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 16 servings.
Can keep refrigerated and just heat up a cup as needed.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Fold into 9 x 11-inch pan or glass dish. Bake in preheated oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour until golden brown.

title: pasta "aglio ed olio"
directions: Heat oil in skillet over low heat, adding garlic.
Stir often until the garlic turns golden, but not burned.
Cook capellini until it's al dente, drain it well and toss it with the oil, garlic, salt, pepper and parsley.
Serve immediately with grated cheese.

title: applesauce oatmeal pancakes
directions: Combine oats, flours and baking powder.
In another bowl, combine milk, applesauce and egg whites; add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour by 1/4 cupfuls onto heated griddle coated with nonstick spray.
Cook until bubbles appear on the top, turn and cook until lightly browned.
Yields 5 servings (2 pancakes each).

title: pineapple nut cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Save 1 cup pecans.
Mound on serving dish. Cover with remaining pecans and chill.
(I roll in pecans which I have chopped in blender.)
Serve with almost any crispy dipper or spread with knife on crackers, celery, green pepper, etc.

title: peking roast
directions: Cut slits completely through meat.
Insert slivers of garlic and onion into these slits.
Put beef in a bowl and pour 1 cup of vinegar over it making sure that vinegar runs down into the little slits.
Place in refrigerator for 24 to 48 hours.
When ready to cook, drain vinegar off and brown meat in iron skillet until almost burned on all sides.
Pour 2 cups of strong black coffee over roast.
Add 2 cups of water and cover.
Cook this slowly at a simmer for 6 hours.* Do not season until 20 minutes before ready to serve.
Then add salt and pepper.
Pan drippings will be very dark and will make excellent gravy.
Roast will fall apart at touch of fork.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and baking powder.
Add sugar very slowly.
Beat until very stiff.
Crush graham crackers and add them and pecans (by folding) to egg mixture.
Add vanilla.

title: chilorio(pork filling for burritos)
directions: The Meat:
Cut the pork into 1-inch cubes.
Cover with water and cook for 45 minutes or until water has evaporated and the meat is barely browned.
Remove meat from the pan and shred it with the tines of 2 forks.
Save the fat that remains.

title: lemon pecan cake
directions: Line greased pan with 2 layers of waxed paper. Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Add all other ingredients and mix well. Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours. First hour, place a pan of water on rack below cake. Remove from oven; let stand 10 minutes. Turn out of pan and remove waxed paper. While warm, spread orange juice over cake and store.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown beef.
Add salt, chili powder and onion.
Cook for several minutes, then add can of chili and cheese.
Cook on low, stirring frequently, until the cheese is melted.

title: impressive jello salad
directions: Mix well cherry jello, strawberry jello and hot water.
Mix marshmallows, bananas, pineapple and nuts all up.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Cook the following on top of stove until thick but do not boil:
sugar, juice from pineapple, eggs, flour and cream cheese.
Stir constantly.
Spread over refrigerated jello evenly. Refrigerate.
Let cool.
On top spread Cool Whip.
Top with coconut.

title: baked johnny bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 10 x 6 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brush margarine on top.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Mix eggs, water, flour, salt and sesame seeds into a batter. Cut chicken into chunks. Heat oil to 375°. Dip chicken into batter and fry until golden brown.

title: sweet potatoes with apples
directions: Place sweet potatoes in a large saucepan; cover with water and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Drain the water and cool the sweet potatoes.
Peel them and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Alternate layers of sweet potatoes and apples in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour the orange juice over the potatoes and apples.
Mix the brown sugar, ginger and cinnamon and sprinkle over the top.
Dot with butter.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cabbage and meatballs
directions: Cut cabbage into small pieces.
Fry in skillet with cooking oil.
When almost tender, place hamburger, rolled into 1-inch balls, on top of cabbage.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with lid.
Turn once or twice and cook until meatballs are done.

title: gingerbread (castle) frosting
directions: Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and water until it holds a stiff peak.
Beat in powdered sugar gradually.
Beat 5-10 minutes; until it holds soft peak.
Cover with damp towel when not using. Keep in tightly covered tupperware if done ahead.
Note:
Hardens when exposed to air.

title: french creams - bar cookies
directions: *I chop up the raisins or dates in the blender with 1 cup of flour added.

title: tuna quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Thaw pie crust as package directs. Prick bottom and sides with a fork.
Bake on cookie sheet for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Combine ingredients and heat for 10 minutes. While sauce is heating, prepare fryer as though frying (salt, dredge and brown in small amount of fat).
Pour sauce over chicken. Cover and cook on top of range or uncovered in oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn chicken several times during cooking.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs in a bowl with a fork until frothy.
Blend in seasoning and corn, adding chunks of butter, half and half and cracker crumbs; mix well.
Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with reserved crumbs; dot generously with more butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute first three ingredients in Dutch oven, add all other ingredients, except chicken.
Simmer over medium heat for 1 hour. Add chicken, heat until hot.
To serve, place tortilla chips in bottom of serving bowl, add soup and garnish with cheese.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients and 3/4 teaspoon of the salt. Shape into 30 or 32 small balls.
Fry a few at a time in the fat in a skillet. Transfer to a plate to keep warm as they are browned.

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add buttermilk and egg, stirring until it is well mixed.
If cracklings are used, season with salt to taste and fold into mixture.
Pour batter into a very hot, well-greased 8-inch skillet.
Bake in a 450° oven for 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin spice bar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add combined flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts; mix well.
Press dough onto bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool completely; cut into bars.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: heavenly hash
directions: You'll need a large bowl to mix this in.
Makes a lot!

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt, 3 tablespoons oil and 2 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover and let rise in warm place 45 minutes.
(Dough is ready when indentation remains when touched.)

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, pineapple, seasoned salt, green pepper and onion in mixer bowl; mix well.
Shape into ball; roll in pecans to coat well.
May add additional 2 tablespoons green pepper, 2 tablespoons green onion and 3/4 cup pineapple if desired.
Yields 1 cheese ball.

title: fruit 'n wheat snack mix(low-fat)
directions: Blend honey and margarine.
Spread cereal on 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Drizzle honey mixture over cereal, tossing to coat well.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in dried fruits; cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: Place strawberries, rum, orange liqueur, lime juice, sugar and ice cubes in blender container. Process until fruit and ice are crushed. Pour into stemmed glasses. Garnish each with a whole strawberry, if desired. Makes 2 servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix the chocolate cake mix, 1/2 cup Carnation milk and butter or margarine together.
Spread 1/2 of batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 9 minutes.
Melt caramels in 1/3 cup Carnation milk and keep warm.
Spread over baked batter.
Sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips over caramel.
Spread on remaining batter and bake 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream punch
directions: Mix all together except ginger ale, adding before serving.
Ice cream is optional, but I put 1 pint to a gallon of punch.
(Recipe makes 1 gallon.)

title: hunnington chicken
directions: Cook macaroni until tender (but not mushy).
Thicken chicken broth with flour; arrange in layers in a 2 to 3-quart casserole. A little poultry seasoning is good, if desired.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with buttered bread crumbs over the top.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add marshmallows.
Add cranberry sauce and nuts.
Gradually thin cream cheese, using part of jello liquid.
When of liquid consistency, add to rest.
Chill.

title: baking powder biscuits(another 1948 recipe)
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add lard and work well into the flour with tips of fingers.
Add milk, roll lightly to 1/2-inch thickness and cut any size desired.
Bake in hot oven 15 minutes.
Note:
These are great!

title: oatmeal nut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until brown.

title: jello salad
directions: In large bowl, add cottage cheese, pineapple and dry Jell-O. Stir well with spoon, then fold in Cool Whip.
Put in dish and refrigerate.

title: orange freeze pie
directions: Dissolve jello in orange juice.
Add ice cream, blending until dissolved.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in mandarin oranges.
Fold in whip cream.
Pour in crust.
Freeze until firm. (I just refrigerate and it's fine.) Serves 8.

title: fruit marmalade
directions: Combine all ingredients except cherries in a heavy pot.
Bring to a boil; reduce and cook for 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Add cherries and seal in sterilized jars.
Process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.
Great little gift!

title: peach-apple cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Melt butter in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Mix peach and apple pie filling; spoon all over the batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked rhubarb
directions: Mix egg, milk, sugar and nutmeg together.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Pour butter on eggs and mix well.
Sprinkle flour over baking dish.
Put rhubarb in dish and pour egg mixture over. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: raspberry oatmeal bars
directions: Combine cake mix and oats.
Stir in melted oleo until mixture is crumbly.
Put about 3 cups of mixture into a Pam sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan and press firmly.
Combine jam and water; spoon over crumb mixture.
Cover with remaining crumb mixture; make top even by patting firmly.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: pork chop skillet meal
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Remove.
Prepare vegetables. Wash rice and brown in pork drippings.
Slice pepper rings and potatoes.
Remove rice from skillet.
Place pork chops in bottom. Layer with peppers, onion, tomatoes, potatoes and rice over them. Season.
Add 1 to 2 cups of water.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: ham deluxe
directions: Prepare ham as directed.
In saucepan, combine apple jelly, mustard, raisins and cherries.
Bring to a boil.
Use this as a topping when the ham is finished cooking.
Serve hot or warm.
Put ham on a serving tray, then pour the topping over the top.
This topping will add a pretty color and a tasty twist to your ham.

title: stove top rice pudding
directions: Cook rice with just enough water to cover.
Cook until tender and all water is gone (watch carefully).
Add milk and bring almost to boiling.
Beat eggs.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and sugar to hot mixture.
Pour a small amount a little at a time into the beaten eggs.
Add egg mixture to milk mixture and continue to heat until it just comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Work together all ingredients.
Knead and place in greased bowl.
Cover with dish towel and let rise for 2 to 3 hours. Pinch off, dip into melted margarine.
Bake on greased pan for about 10 minutes or until brown at 425°.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Put sugar, syrup and milk in saucepan; let stand until sugar is melted.
Shave chocolate into mixture.
Put over fire and bring to boiling point.
Do not stir.
Let boil 2 minutes and add butter.
Cook until soft ball is formed in cold water.
Remove from fire.
Line long pan with marshmallows; sprinkle with nuts. Let fudge cool slightly in pan of cold water while beating.
Fudge must be quite warm when poured over marshmallows.
When cool, cut into 2-inch squares.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender, blending until smooth and thick.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.
This is just like the "Eagle Brand" milk you buy in the store.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup and Knox gelatine, then add cream cheese until cream cheese is melted.
Let it sit for 5 minutes.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Then pour into a mold and place in the refrigerator to chill at least 6 hours.

title: toll house pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: dutch oven sweet bread
directions: Soften yeast in
tepid	water and add 1 teaspoon sugar. Mix milk, margarine,
sugar and salt.
Add yeast mixture.
Add eggs. Add flour to
make	a soft dough.
Let stand 10 minutes and
then knead.
Let
rise
until
double.
Shape
into three sections
and braid.
Place in14-inch Dutch oven.
Brush dough with melted margarine.	Place lid on oven and let rise for 20 minutes.	Place 12	coals
on
top and 6 coals on the bottom. Bake 45
minutes while
rotating a quarter turn every 15 minutes.

title: judith's homemade tomato sauce
directions: In a large skillet, put a little olive oil and 1 garlic clove; cook until the garlic is golden brown.
Set aside.

title: potato-leek soup
directions: Cook vegetables in enough water to keep from sticking until tender.
Add chicken broth and seasonings.
Add Accent while cooking.

title: aunt irene's pound cake
directions: Combine sweet milk, sugar, margarine and eggs and beat well. Then mix in vanilla and salt.
Add baking powder and flour.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: coconut delight
directions: Blend margarine and flour with pastry blender into coarse meal consistency.
Add pecans and press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, reserving 1/2 cup walnuts. Chill, then shape into ball.
Roll ball in reserved walnuts. Refrigerate for at least a couple of hours before serving.

title: date puddin'
directions: Mix all gud 'n bake at 375° fur about 45 minutes.
Serve hot 'r cold wid whipped cream 'r hard sauce...to bout 8 folks.

title: mushroom stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/4 pound butter in skillet.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring often, until mushrooms turn very dark and absorb butter.
Remove from heat and add 3/4 cup of bread crumbs and nutmeg.
Divide mushroom stuffing into 8 portions and place in center of each piece of chicken.
Fold chicken around stuffing and place seam side down in casserole pan. Melt remaining 4 tablespoons of butter and brush over chicken. Sprinkle with remaining 3/4 cup of bread crumbs.
Pour cream over the chicken.
Bake approximately 45 minutes.

title: chicken and vegetable fricassee
directions: Wash chicken.
Coat in mixture of flour, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Brown in melted margarine.
Add water.
Cover. Simmer 40 minutes.
Add carrots, peas and onion.
(Add 1/2 cup water if liquid evaporates during cooking.) Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Stir evaporated milk into vegetables in skillet.
Heat to serving. Pour over chicken.

title: chicken with wine sauce
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Set aside.
Spray a large skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Add mushrooms, basil and garlic.
Cook over medium heat until onion is tender.
Stir in chicken broth, wine, salt and pepper.
Arrange chicken in.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and cook over low heat until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Transfer chicken and vegetables to a serving platter; keep warm.
Measure cooking liquid.
Add water to equal 1 cup, if necessary.
Pour in skillet.
Combine cornstarch and 1 tablespoon water.
Stir into cooking liquid in skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more. Serve over chicken.
Makes 5 servings.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Sift flour and cornstarch, beat butter until creamy.
Add sugar and beat; gradually add flour.
Knead with hand, then pack in pan until it is 1/3-inch thick.
Mark in squares; prick with fork.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° oven.

title: yellow squash casserole 2
directions: Boil, drain and mash squash.
Saute in a little margarine onion and pepper.
Add to squash.
Add mayonnaise, egg, pimento, cheese and sugar.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together until pudding and Tang are dissolved.
Refrigerate until time to serve.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pop-up pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour and sugar.
Add milk.
Stir to blend.
Place in a Pyrex dish. Spoon in fruit.
Bake at 425° until brown.
Crust will rise to the top.

title: shoyu chicken wings
directions: Clean wings, separating at joints.
Bring all ingredients (not chicken) to boil.
Then add wings and simmer 40 minutes.

title: dream pie squares
directions: Line a 9-inch square pan with whole graham crackers.
Prepare whipped topping.
Mix with 1 cup of the milk as directed on package using large mixer bowl.
Add remaining 1 3/4 cups milk and the pudding mix.
Blend; then beat at high speed for 2 minutes. Reserve a few oranges for garnish; dice remaining oranges and fold into pudding mixture with nuts.
Spoon 1/2 the mixture over crackers; add another layer of crackers, then remaining pudding mixture.
Garnish with reserved orange sections.
Chill 4 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Make instant pudding in bowl by directions.
Fold in Cool Whip and sour cream.
Pour over and mix together wafers and bananas.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Cut bacon slices in halves.
Wrap around a bunch of green beans (approximately 16 beans) and secure with toothpick.
Make glaze with margarine, sugar, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Pour over beans.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 375°.
Bake, uncovered, last few minutes to brown.
Serves 6.

title: aunt vesta's casserole
directions: In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer in order given.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: kids champagne
directions: Add bottles of soda water to the apple juice concentrate. Keep this "champagne" in tightly capped (wine) bottles to insure retention of fizz.
This is a good substitute for soft drinks.

title: chili seasoning mix and chili with beans
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients for the chili mix.
Store unused portion in tight container in cool dry place. Yields 4 batches. Can store mix until ready to prepare.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Combine the first four ingredients. Line pie plate with bottom crust; add apples, Pour juice mixture over apples; dot with margarine. Roll out remaining pastry to fit top of pie; cut slits or an apple shape in top. Place over filling; seal and flute the edges. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes. Increase temperature to 400°; bake 15 - 20 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together.
Add tomatoes and green peppers.
Cover and cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Add corn and seasoning and stir well.
Cook slowly for another 30 minutes. Stir often and water may be added, if too thick.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
In separate bowl, mix sugar and cream cheese.
Mix Dream Whip as directed on box.
Add creamed mixture to Dream Whip.
Spread over cool crust.
Top with cherry filling.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight is best. Hollow out center of bread; fill with dip.
Use pieces of bread for dipping.

title: toffee crunch
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Layer saltine crackers.
Boil together brown sugar and butter for 3 minutes.
Pour sugar mixture slowly over the crackers and bake for 5 to 7 minutes in a 400°. Put chocolate chips over the top and spread when melted.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over top.
Score while warm and place in refrigerator until cool.
Break apart.

title: north carolina's melt-in-your-mouth chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in Pam-sprayed 6 x 10-inch baking dish. In saucepan, mix soup and broth and bring to a boil. Pour over chicken. Mix flour, pepper, buttermilk and margarine like a batter. Spoon over casserole. Bake at 425° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in thin slices.
Place in a deep casserole dish.
Combine sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg; add to potatoes, along with a cup of water.
Cut butter in pieces and layer over ingredients.
Cover with your pastry.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: mama's old fashioned coconut pound cake
directions: Have eggs and butter at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Spray tube pan with Pam.
Cream butter and sugar together well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well. Add flour, salt, soda, sour cream and vanilla.
Blend.
Stir in coconut. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Put ingredients in a double boiler and mix with the mixer on high, while heating until icing peaks.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and spread over any cake.

title: easy dessert (no cook)
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Combine water, sugar and pie filling; boil for 5 minutes. Stir occasionally, remove from heat and stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Add pineapple, nuts and Coke.
Place in mold or dish. Refrigerate to jell.
Will keep a long time in fridge.

title: date 'n' pear bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour bottom of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine all ingredients.
Stir 50 to 75 strokes until moist.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 350°
for 55 to 65 minutes. Cool 15 minutes before turn out of pan.

title: souperior meal loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Place half of batter in pan.
On top drop 1/2 can of whole cranberry sauce.
Cover with rest of batter.
Drop rest of sauce on top and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: champagne punch
directions: In large punch bowl, mix all ingredients.
Float strawberries on top.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix well.
This can be used as a barbecue sauce for baking or used as a dip for your chicken or pork.

title: greek vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the tomatoes, green peppers, cucumber, olives and cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; toss lightly.
In small bowl or screw-top jar, combine the parsley, oregano, garlic, oil and lemon juice; blend well.
Pour dressing over vegetables; toss well.
Let stand for 1 hour to marinate. Serve at room temperature.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: whole wheat health bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Pour boiling water over salt, sugar and shortening. When lukewarm, add the yeast and stir in the wheat flour gradually.
Mix to a stiff dough and knead until smooth, adding more flour, if necessary.
Let rise in a warm place until double in bulk.
Shape into 2 loaves and place in greased and floured pans.
Let rise again until double in bulk and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until the bread shrinks from pan.

title: gingered shrimp
directions: In wok over medium-high heat, heat oil 1 minute.
Add ginger; cook 1 minute.
Add shrimp and cook 4 minutes.
With slotted spoon, remove shrimp; set aside.
Add pineapple, snow peas and pepper to wok.
Cook 1 minute; in measuring cup, stir pineapple juice, cornstarch, vinegar, sugar and salt until smooth.
Add to wok.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp.
Cook 3 minutes until sauce thickens.

title: pink salad
directions: Beat together all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: homemade stuffing
directions: Lay out bread the night before and let dry out.
Melt butter, onions and celery.
Saute.
Blend sauteed mixture with broken up pieces of bread in a large pan.
Pour in chicken broth until bread is mushy.
Add eggs and blend together well.
Add poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Butter bowl and place dressing in bowl.
Cover and bake until brown in 350° oven.
Makes one casserole bowl.

title: cowboy coffee cake
directions: Overlap 1 can of biscuits in a greased Bundt pan.
Combine nuts, cinnamon, oil and brown sugar.
Spread between biscuits. Place next can of biscuits on top of sugar mixture, then spread another layer of sugar.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: billy's chili
directions: Put all ingredients in a pot and simmer until peppers and celery are tender.
If it gets too thick, add tomato juice.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Combine sugar, butter and egg yolks.
Then add lemon rind and juice, flour and milk.
Mix this all together, then last of all, add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 2 pie pans.
Bake in slow oven for about 3/4 of an hour.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly with a wire whisk or mixer in top of a double boiler.
Add sugar, flour, melted butter and lemon juice. Mix well.
Blend in milk and cook about 15 minutes over rapidly boiling water, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Allow filling to cool.
Fold in sour cream and pour into baked pie crust.

title: hot mushroom dip
directions: Fry bacon, drain and reserve 2 tablespoons fat in skillet. Add mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Cook on medium heat until mushroom liquid is evaporated.
Mix in flour, salt and pepper. Add cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce.
Reduce heat to low.
Stir until melted and combined.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream and bacon.
Serve warm with crackers.
Can be refrigerated and reheated slowly.

title: italian hebrew soup(borscht)
directions: Simmer the beets in the salted water and vinegar for 20 minutes.
Pass through a sieve (or puree in an electric blender). Beat the eggs briskly in a large bowl and pour into the beet broth, beating all the time.
Season with salt and pepper and chill.
Serve ice cold and give each guest a small bowl of hot, boiled potatoes that have been swirled in margarine.
Eat a little potato with each spoonful of soup.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cathedral window candy
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips.
Cool slightly.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Divide into balls.
Spread on foil and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Roll into long rolls (logs) in foil and refrigerate.
Slice.
Makes 3 to 4 logs.

title: danish pastry apple bars (streusel)
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg yolk and mix in 2/3 cup milk.
Stir into flour mixture.
On floured surface, roll out half of dough to fit into 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with cereal and top with apples.
Mix sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle on top of apples.

title: rocky road pie
directions: Pour half and half into large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, about 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream (Cool Whip), chocolate chips, marshmallows and nuts.
Spoon into pie crust.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer and let stand about 10 minutes before serving.
Store any leftover pie in freezer.

title: topsy-turvy cake
directions: Mix apple filling, spices and lemon juice.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: cheesy zucchini bake
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic powder.
Drain and set aside. Cut zucchini in 1/4-inch slices (do not peel) and cook for 5 minutes in water.
Drain.
In a greased casserole dish, layer in 1/2 of meat, 1/2 of the zucchini and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Mix soup with 1/4 cup water and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: mexican dish
directions: Cook meat until brown; drain grease.
Add other ingredients. Cook on top of stove for 10 minutes until mixed well and cheese is melted.
Crush chips in bottom of pan.
Pour mixture on top.
Cook at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tuna supper salad
directions: Shred lettuce in large salad bowl.
Layer tomato, onion and cucumber.
Sprinkle tuna fish over salad.
Sprinkle grated cheese over the salad.
Season with salt, pepper, sugar and Season-All. Slice eggs around top of the salad.

title: chicken and mushroom risotto
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken pieces in butter; remove chicken.
In same skillet, brown rice, onion and carrot until rice is brown, stirring constantly.
Stir in broth, soup and pepper; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add peas and chicken; cover and simmer 5 more minutes.

title: refrigerator relish
directions: Chop in food processor separately the red peppers, green peppers, celery and onions.
Mix together red and green peppers, tomatoes, celery and onions.
Add 1/4 cup salt.
Set mixture aside for 12 hours.
Drain mixture and add sugar, vinegar and mustard seed.
Mixture gets spicier as it sets.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine first five ingredients in medium bowl; beat eggs, sugar, pumpkin and oil in large bowl.
Add dry ingredients until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted is clean.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Into
a large bowl, sift the flour, soda, baking powder and oats.
Cream the shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs and vanilla. Gradually	add
dry ingredients.
Mix until crumbly, then	add chips
and	nuts.
Form
into walnut size balls and place
on
an oiled baking sheet.
Wet a flat bottom glass and dip into sugar. Flatten out each cookie with the glass.
Bake at
for
10 minutes or until slightly browned.	Cool on sheet, then slip off rack.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix together oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix well and stir in plum baby food.
Add raisins and pecans.
Place in tube pan and cook on 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: sandra's baked beans
directions: Mix all together.
Sweeten to taste.
Allow to cook on low in crock-pot for several hours.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix bran, sugar, soda, salt and flour.
Add eggs, shortening and milk.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
May store in refrigerator 4 to 6 weeks.

title: colorful veggie bake
directions: Prepare vegetables according to package directions. Drain. Place half in a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. In a small saucepan, combine cheese and 4 tablespoons butter. Cook and stir over low heat until melted. Pour half over vegetables. Repeat layers. Melt remaining butter. Toss with cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over the top. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Mix milk, vanilla pudding and Cool Whip.
Add creamed mixture and mix well. Place crushed cookies in bottom of sand bucket, then layer with cream mixture; continue, ending with cookies on top.
Refrigerate overnight or freeze, taking out 1/2 hour before serving.
Decorate with flower and gummy worms.

title: meatballs and noodles
directions: Mix together ground meat, milk, bread crumbs, chopped onion, salt and pepper.
Make into balls; roll in flour in small amount of fat.
Fry until brown; remove from pan.
Leave small amount of fat in frypan.
Add 1 can vegetable soup and rest of canned milk.
Heat until it begins to boil.
Pour over 3 or 4 cups cooked and drained noodles.
Cook and drain noodles.
Place meatballs on top and serve hot.

title: pie crust
directions: Add flour, salt and Crisco.
Work until it is crumb like. Gradually add the milk.
Add just enough flour to make on board. Makes 2 pie shells.

title: kidney pudding(a specialty of the scots and brits among us!)
directions: Saute beef, onion, green pepper and garlic in a skillet until browned.
Remove corn from ears and add with remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together 3/4 cup margarine and 1 cup sugar.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time with sour cream and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon, chopped pecans and butter.
Bake at 325° approximately 1 hour.

title: cheese noodles
directions: Mix eggs with white sauce; add cheese and blend.
Pour over noodles and mix lightly.
Add pimento and green pepper and blend. Bake 35 to 40 minutes over water.

title: best chess pie
directions: Mix
together
and bake in uncooked pie shell for about an hour at 350°.

title: turkey royale
directions: Combine dressing, butter and water.
Toss until dressing is moist.
Place 1/2 in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Dice turkey or chicken and combine with onion, celery, mayonnaise and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread over layer of dressing, then scatter remaining dressing on top.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour evenly over casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook meat and onion in butter until soft. Blend flour, pepper, milk, salt, eggs, Worcestershire sauce and 1 cup cheese. Combine with meat and pour into pie shell. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top. Cook at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: spiced tea
directions: Add 2 1/4 pounds sugar to each gallon after mixing.
Pour into a barrel or crock until filled to top; cover with cheesecloth. Allow to ferment; fill with water every other day until fermentation ceases to run over.
Allow to stand a total of 30 to 35 days.
Take up, put in bottles and seal.
Makes first class wine.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl, cover and refrigerate. Serve cold.

title: snack pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put a little grease or oil on a baking sheet.
Pat each biscuit into a 4-inch circle.
Put each circle on the sheet.

title: cheddar appetizer
directions: Bring cheese and butter to room temperature.
Beat cheese and butter with electric mixer until combined.
Add milk, onion, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce.
Beat until smooth. Pack in a container.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Serve at room temperature with assorted crackers.

title: sausage stuffing
directions: Cook onions, celery and apples in broth 4 to 5 minutes. Lightly brown sausage in heavy skillet.
Drain off drippings. Combine with bread crumbs and then add broth.
Mix lightly.
More liquid may be added if stuffing needs more moisture.
Use stuffing for turkey, chicken or pork chops or place in a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered or until browned.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Put vanilla wafer in bottom of cupcake paper.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Place 2 tablespoons of mixture on top of wafer.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped nuts. Refrigerate.
Makes 24 tarts.

title: no bake cookies
directions: You will need wax paper for this recipe.

title: corn-crisped chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces into evaporated milk.
Mix corn flakes, salt and pepper and roll chicken in mixture.
Place in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until tender when pierced with a fork.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Rinse wild rice; mix rice and water.
Brown hamburger with celery; drain.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Mix all together in large roaster and add soy sauce to taste.
Bake at 350° for approximately 2 hours.

title: "good and filling" corned beef, potatoes and onion stew
directions: Add corned beef to potatoes and onions.
Add enough water to cover ingredients; season to taste and cook 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine ingredients and serve hot.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and sugar.
Pour over rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour to give raisins time to plump up.

title: cream cheese fingers
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar and egg yolk; set aside. Melt oleo; set aside.
Combine 1 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Set aside.
Roll out each slice of bread until flat with rolling pin.
Spread each slice with cream cheese mixture; roll up jelly roll fashion.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Take bone out of salmon.
Mix mayonnaise, soup and egg.
Add bread crumbs, onion, pepper and lemon juice.
Stir.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add sauce and let simmer.
Cook desired amount of spaghetti and drain.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir in sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and potatoes.
Mix in flour.
Knead on floured surface until smooth.
Roll in oil.
Put in bowl.
Cover.
Put in refrigerator for 1 1/2 to 2 hours before making into rolls.
Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours or double.
Bake in a 400° oven for 12 to 13 minutes.
May be kept in refrigerator.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together until light, then add the egg, beating until thick.
Stir in the cream.

Sift the flour with the baking powder and salt; add with the cardamom to the creamed mixture, mixing until a stiff dough forms. Chill thoroughly. Shape the chilled dough into small balls (about 1 inch in diameter) and arrange on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in a moderately hot oven (375°) for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden.
If you wish, you may brush the cookies with egg before baking to give them a shiny glaze.
Makes 48.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot. Stir to mix well.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours. (High 4 to 5 hours; auto 6 hours.)

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Using palm of hand, flatten chicken to even thickness.
Dip chicken into egg, then into crumbs to coat.

title: apple carrot muffins
directions: In a bowl mix all dry ingredients, in another bowl mix remaining ingredients except apple and carrot.
To the dry ingredients add liquids and mix; fold in apples and carrots.
Line a 12 muffin tin with paper muffin liners or spray with Pam.
Fill cups half full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pineapple cheese delight
directions: Mix whipped topping, cream cheese and vanilla in bowl on medium speed for 1 minute.
Add crushed pineapple and blend at low speed for 1 minute.
Put mixed ingredients in prepared graham cracker crust.
Cover and refrigerate until cold or firm.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, let eggs warm to room temperature, about 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour with baking soda, cloves, cinnamon, ginger, and nutmeg.
At high speed, beat eggs with sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in oil and pumpkin to blend well.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture just until combined.
Pour into an ungreased 9-inch tube pan. Bake about one hour, or until surface springs back when gently pressed with fingertips.
Cool cake completely in pan.
With spatula, carefully loosen cake from pan; remove.
Place on cake plate, frost with Cream Cheese Frosting and decorate with pecan or walnut halves.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add olives, chili powder, salt and tomato sauce.
Place buttered tortilla in casserole, top with meat sauce and cheese.
Alternate layers.
Garnish top with shredded cheese.
Bake in oven at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes with cover on casserole dish.

title: chocolate-filled snowballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except kisses and powdered sugar.
Use about 1 tablespoon of dough to shape around kiss and roll into a ball.
Make sure kiss is completely covered.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes, until set but not brown.
Roll in powdered sugar when completely cool.

title: baklava(pastry filled with almond and walnut meats; middle east)
directions: In large bowl, mix nuts with sugar and spices.
Brush bottom of a 10 x 6-inch baking pan with melted butter.
Place six sheets in bottom of pan, brushing each with butter.
Sprinkle a thin layer of nut mixture on top of the sixth buttered sheet.
Cover with one pastry sheet; brush with butter and again, sprinkle with the nut mixture.
Continue this alternate process until all nuts are used. Finish dessert with six to eight filo, placing one on top of the other and brushing each with butter.
With a serrated knife, cut Baklava into strips 1-inch wide and cut these strips diagonally to form small diamond shaped pieces.
Bake in a very slow oven (300°) for approximately 1 hour.
Let cool.
Pour Honey Syrup over it, reserving 3/4 cup.
Return the 3/4 cup of Honey Syrup to heat and boil five minutes longer.
Finish glazing with remaining syrup. Yields about 80.
Cool 6 hours before using.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender and drain.
Add diced eggs, onions, bell pepper, pickle and olives.
Add Season-All, salt, pepper, mayonnaise and mustard.

title: impossible cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate.
Beat all ingredients together on high speed.
Pour into ungreased plate.
Bake until puffed center is dry, about 30 minutes.
Spread a can of pie filling carefully over it and cool.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy. Add sugar.
Scald sweet milk. Add to egg mixture. Add evaporated milk, salt, vanilla and nuts. Freeze until firm.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix ingredients together; chill.
Roll batter in walnut size balls and dip in sugar.
Place sugar side up on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° about 12 to 15 minutes.
These flatten and crackle on top.

title: chewy turtle cake
directions: Pour boiling water on chocolate, stirring until melted.
Cool. Grease and flour rectangular pan, 12 x 9 x 2-inch.
Beat sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat in chocolate mixture and vanilla at low speed.
Mix in flour and baking soda and salt alternately with buttermilk, beating after each addition until batter is smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Pour into pan.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350° or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Beat butter and cream cheese together in a mixing bowl until well blended.
Add sugar to mixture; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and mix.
Blend in vanilla.
Sift flour and salt together; blend into mixture.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Check with a toothpick.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Turn out on a wire rack to cool completely.

title: kalu (hawaiian) pork
directions: Place roast on heavy duty aluminum foil, in baking dish, with Ti or spinach leaves under roast.
Mix soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, ginger and liquid smoke.
Pour over roast.
Sprinkle with rock salt.
Cover with leaves. Wrap tightly in foil.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours. Remove leaves. Shred roast and use liquid to pour over meat.

title: hormel chili dip
directions: Spread the cream cheese evenly in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour over the chili.
Top with shredded cheese.
Place in microwave for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with favorite chips.

title: ground beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in large casserole.
Pour soup over top. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 400°.

title: hot mulled cranberry drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; heat to boiling point. Pour into mugs.
Serve with cinnamon sticks.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients together and put in covered baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° in covered dish for 45 to 60 minutes, until set.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: kraut salad
directions: Beat sugar and vinegar until clear.
Cool and pour over the remaining ingredients.
Let set for at least 4 hours before serving.

title: italian potato wedgies
directions: On a dinner plate, combine oil, Italian seasoning, paprika and salt.
Add potato wedges, turning to coat with mixture; arrange in a spoke-like fashion, cut sides down.
Cook, covered with wax paper, on High for 4 to 5 minutes, until tender; rotate each wedge halfway through cooking.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Let stand 3 minutes.
If you like, serve with catsup or tomato sauce. Makes 1 serving.

title: brown sugar applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add brown
sugar.
Add
egg.
Combine
2 1/2 cups flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture alternately
with applesauce, beginning and ending with flour. Drench raisins
and
nuts
with remaining 1/2 cup flour.
Fold into batter.
Pour
