into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: spinach squares
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until light or medium brown.
Let cool slightly and cut into small squares.

title: baked squirrel
directions: Note:
One-half squirrel or more for each serving.

title: robyn sharkey's waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix beef crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape into balls.
Melt shortening in large skillet.
Brown and cook meatballs.
Remove meatballs; keep warm.
Pour off fat.
Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Stir in reserved pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together instant pudding and juice from pineapple.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix together, then add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Make day before and keep in refrigerator.

title: mama's lemon custard pie
directions: Using a spoon, cream sugar and butter in a bowl until well mixed.
Add flour, salt, egg yolks and milk; mix well.
Add lemon juice; mix well.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; gently fold into lemon mixture.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Store in the refrigerator.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: garden sauté
directions: In large skillet or wok, melt butter over medium heat. Add red pepper, celery and asparagus, if used.
Stir-fry about 3 minutes. Add zucchini, mushrooms and seasonings. Use more butter, if necessary, and stir-fry 2 minutes longer.

title: cheese ball
directions: Set cream cheese and Cheddar cheese out to soften.
Chop green pepper, pimento and onion real fine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into log or ball and chill.
If desired, roll into chopped pecans.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding per directions on box.
Mix in Cool Whip and sour cream.
Layer vanilla wafers, pudding and bananas in a dish. Sprinkle wafer crumbs on top for looks.

title: pink salad
directions: Drain the pineapple.
Heat juice. Add marshmallows. Stir until melted.
Add dry Jell-O. Stir until dissolved. Cool.
Mix pineapple, cheese and nuts. Add to Jell-O mixture.
Fold in whipped cream. Chill.

title: strawberry kool-aid vodka slush
directions: Boil water and sugar; remove from heat and add remaining ingredients and freeze.
Serve with 7-Up.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Preheat oven
to
In a large bowl combine 2 cups flour and yeast.
In pan heat milk, sugar, oleo and salt until warm. Stir.
Add
to
flour
mixture.
Add
eggs; beat at low speed 1/2 minute; then beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in remaining flour,
as
much
as
you can mix in.
Turn out on a floured board and knead in enough flour to make elastic.
Put in greased
bowl; let rise until double.
Punch down, shape in half, let
rest
10 minutes.
Shape into rolls; cover and let rise until double in size.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil, zucchini and flour together.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pans at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaf pans or 1 tube pan.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell; sprinkle some sugar and cinnamon on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: In large skillet or Dutch oven, brown the spareribs well on both sides.
Add sliced onion, brown sugar, catsup, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add 2 cups water; cover and simmer about 2 hours, until ribs are tender.
Remove spareribs and thicken the juice as would gravy.
Delicious served with mashed potatoes!
(Also cooks up nicely in a crock-pot.)

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine rhubarb, 1 1/2 cups of sugar, tapioca, egg yolks and lemon juice in top of a double boiler.
Cook until done.
Stir in butter.
Cool mixture, then pour into baked pie shell.

title: white potato pie
directions: Peel and cook potatoes as you would for mashed potatoes. Mash so there are no lumps.
Add sugar, vanilla, eggs, milk and first cinnamon.
Beat until mixture is creamy.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle top with the small amounts of sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 375° until firm.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until apples are done.

title: mama's peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in long cake pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Place peaches in pan.

title: flaming bananas
directions: Put butter and brown sugar into chafing dish or 8-inch skillet.
Heat, stirring, until sugar and butter are combined. Add 1/4 cup dark rum.
Slice bananas into pan and simmer 7 or 8 minutes.
Heat 2 tablespoons of brandy or rum in a large spoon. Ignite and turn into pan.
Stir gently until flame burns out. Serve at once over hard-frozen vanilla ice cream.
Serves 6.
Very showy.

title: a quick dessert(cherry)
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Melt marshmallows with sweetened condensed milk over low heat; stirring constantly.
When melted, add graham cracker crumbs, pecans and cherries.
Press in a loaf pan that has been lightly greased.
When set, cut into small squares.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, eggs, oil, apricot nectar and sugar about 2 minutes on medium speed.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour in a tube pan.
Mix powdered sugar and lemon juice together and drizzle over the top of the cake after it has cooled a bit, but still warm.

title: pork chops with mushroom rice
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Heat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, mix rice, water, milk and soup, then lay browned pork chops on top and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: art's swedish meatballs
directions: *Stores don't tell you about pork, but if you know a butcher or you're doing your own, leave out 90% of the fat!

title: shanghai noodles with spicy beef sauce
directions: Heat wok or large skillet until hot; add the oil, garlic, ginger root and pepper flakes.
Saute about 5 seconds.
Add onion; stir-fry until onion is transparent.
Crumble in ground beef. Stir-fry until the meat is light brown.
In a small bowl, combine 1/4 cup chicken broth, hoisin sauce, soy sauce and sherry/broth. Stir into meat mixture.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Meanwhile, dissolve cornstarch in remaining chicken broth.
Slowly stir into meat mixture.
Cook and stir until the sauce is thick.
In separate bowl combine the hot vermicelli and sesame oil.
Pour sauce over top.
Toss gently to combine.
Serve topped with green onions.

title: pan-broiled steak
directions: Use thick skillet.
Place on high temperature until margarine is melted and steak is seared on both sides.
Cook to desired doneness.

title: parsley broiled chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Brush chicken generously with mixture on both sides.
Put skin side down and broil 10-inches from heat source, 20 minutes.
Turn skin side up.
Brush with additional oil mixture.
Broil 20 minutes longer or until tender.

title: oriental sea bass or salmon
directions: Whisk soy sauce, olive oil, garlic, ginger and vinegar together in measuring cup.
Arrange fish in a shallow dish.
Pour on marinade and turn to coat.
Cover and refrigerate to marinate for 30 minutes.

title: pecan topped grahams
directions: In a small saucepan, combine butter and sugar over low heat until butter is melted.
Stir well.
Remove from heat; stir in corn syrup and pecans.
Place 1 tablespoon of mixture on top of each graham cracker.
Spread to edges with spatula.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake for 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool, then break into squares.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350°.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Cream oleo and add beaten eggs, then flour and nuts.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Chop onions and saute in 1 tablespoon cooking oil until soft and clear.
Add bottle of ketchup.
Fill bottle full of water and add to ketchup and onions.
Add rest of ingredients and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 45 minutes.

title: mexican dish
directions: Fry ground meat until done; drain.
Add chili powder, soup and green chilies.
Line a long baking dish with Doritos.
Pour ground meat mixture over Doritos.
Heat in a 350° oven until bubbling. Spread cheese over top and put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together, then alternate milk and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until fork comes out clean.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Brown the ground beef; drain. Add beans and picante sauce to beef.
Put in baking dish. Smooth sour cream on top.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic in butter until tender.
Wash rice thoroughly until water is clear.
Add rice, tomatoes, parsley, seasonings and beef broth to vegetables.
Simmer about 40 minutes. Cube smoked sausage and fry it in a saucepan until brown. Drain.
Add sausage to rice mixture and simmer for another 20 minutes (add water during cooking time if mixture becomes too dry).
Serves 6.

title: quick and easy rosemary chicken
directions: Sprinkle spices over chicken placed in oven
pan.
Place real butter cubes directly on chicken.
All will melt together to make a creamy rich sauce.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cook slower and chicken is more moist.

title: mock chop suey
directions: Cook hamburger.
Drain.
Put in casserole dish.
Add other ingredients to hamburger, except chow mein noodles.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 350°.
Put chow mein noodles on top of casserole and cook another ten minutes uncovered.

title: holiday relish
directions: Place all ingredients in processor bowl with metal blade.
Be sure to include orange peel.
Process to desired coarseness.
Fine is about 15 to 20 seconds.
You may have to scrape bowl down twice.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Measure the Bisquick in a mixing bowl.
Open the beer and drink 1/3; only 1/3!
Add remainder of the beer to the bowl and mix well.
Pour mixture into greased muffin pan, filling each section only 2/3 full (yeast in the beer will rise dough). Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until browned.
Makes 1 dozen biscuits.
Goes well with stew or chili.

title: noodle con carne
directions: Cook meat and onion in a large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix and simmer, covered, until noodles are soft.
You may have to add some water.

title: chocolate pecan brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Place chocolate pieces and butter in pot over boiling water.
Melt together; mix well.
Place eggs and sugar in mixing bowl and beat until thick and lemon in color.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Stir in nuts until well blended.
Pour into 8-inch square pan that has been greased.
If you have extra pecans, sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt margarine; add Worcestershire sauce and chili powder. Pour over mixture.
sprinkle with salt and garlic salt.
Cook at 200° for 1 hour, stirring often.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in ungreased Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Test with toothpick.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil fryer in salted water, debone, and cut in small piece. Saute onion.
In saucepan mix tomatoes, soups and onion.
Heat to boiling.
In baking dish, layer Doritos and chicken.
Pour soup mixture over; cover with cheese.
Pour chicken broth over all. Heat in 375° oven until cheese melts and bubbles around edge, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: turkey soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cover with water; cook until vegetables are done.
Some water may have to be added while cooking.
Serve hot.
An excellent way to use leftover turkey.

title: brandy balls
directions: Grind vanilla wafers and mix well with remaining ingredients except sugar.
Form into balls.
Roll in sugar, cocoa or nuts. Place in a tightly covered container.
Makes about 60.

title: bean dip
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Pour hot mixture into blender container.
Add cheese and Tabasco sauce.
Cover and blend on high speed until smooth, about 20 to 45 seconds.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with pie filling.
Make a day ahead.
Add bananas just before serving.
Serves approximately 10.

title: apple crisps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange apples in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake until topping is golden brown and apples are tender, approximately 30 minutes.

title: pickled watermelon rind
directions: Peel watermelon rind and cut in small pieces.
Peel and soak rind in lime overnight (1 gallon water).
Soak 5 hours in plain ice water.
Cook 30 to 60 minutes in water to cover with 1 cup of vinegar or until tender.
Drain 30 minutes.
Mix 1 pint vinegar, 6 cups sugar, 1 teaspoon whole cloves, 1 box stick cinnamon and 1 box whole allspice.
Let boil.
Add rind and let boil about 30 minutes. Put in jars and seal at once.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix ingredients at medium speed until well blended.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 3 layers at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix the mushroom and celery soups, milk and rice in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken, skin side up, on top of soup mixture.
Sprinkle onion mix over chicken.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, margarine, shortening and eggs in bowl.
Stir in flour.
Shape by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Mix 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon. Roll balls into this mixture.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set, 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet.

title: hot cinnamon cider
directions: Heat apple cider to boiling.
Add cinnamon candies to melt. Stir.
Use enough candy and obtain sweetness and redness desired.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, egg yolks, vanilla and melted margarine. Add egg whites that are beaten.
Grease a dish and pour ingredients into it.
Mix topping (last 4 items) and pour on sweet potatoes.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sangria
directions: Traditionally served in a glass pitcher with a wooden spoon.

title: cheese daisies(6 dozen)
directions: Cream butter and 2 cheeses with hand.
Add unsifted flour, salt and red pepper.
Mix well.
Shape in 4 long rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and chill 1/2 hour.
Slice like a silver dollar.
Put pecan half on top of each, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes or until tan around the edges (will get bitter if cooked too long).
Take up while hot and cool on Scott towels.

title: sausage, cheese & sauerkraut balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together in a very large bowl; making sure sauerkraut is mixed in very well.
Form into balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake around 20 minutes or until balls are golden brown. Some ovens take longer. You can freeze uncooked balls if you wish.
One recipe makes a lot.
32 ounces of sauerkraut = about 6 cups.

title: breakfast raisin muffins
directions: Bring water to a boil; add raisins and return to a boil. Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally.
Drain, reserving liquid; add water to measure 1/2 cup if necessary. Dissolve soda in liquid.
Combine next 4 ingredients; stir in raisins and make a well in center of mixture.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
about 1 dozen.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Melt oleo; add brown sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and beaten eggs.
Mix good; then add black walnuts to mixture.
Bake in a greased pan approximately 40 minutes at 325° to 350°, depending on oven.
After cake cools, cut in squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: chocolate creme de menthes
directions: Melt over hot (not boiling) water the Nestle morsels.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream.
Stir in mint flavored liqueur.
Transfer to small bowl.
Chill until thickened, about 30 minutes.
Fill pastry bag with decorative tip; pipe 1-inch candies onto foil-lined cookie sheets.
Chill until ready to serve.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen candies.

title: meat balls
directions: Season the meat with the spices and add half the onion.
Add the egg.
Squnch it all together and then make 1 1/2-inch meat balls (seems to make between 10 and 12 of them).
Place in a shallow baking dish and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Flip the balls over with a spoon.

title: osgood pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Cream margarine with first mixture. Add eggs.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: pork sticks
directions: Slice pork across grain into 1/4-inch thick strips.
Mix 7-Up, soy sauce, garlic, lemon juice, Accent and pepper together.
Pour mixture over pork strips and marinate 12 to 24 hours.
Place pork strips on bamboo sticks.
Barbecue over hot coals.
Before pork is finished cooking, brush with barbecue sauce.

title: peggy's ginger cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add the molasses and egg and beat well. Add the sifted dry ingredients. Roll teaspoonful of dough in sugar and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: pudding ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in churn and freeze.
Add fruit if desired.

title: colorful and chewy potato salad(makes about 9 pounds)
directions: Peel potatoes, cook until done, but firm.
While potatoes are cooking, put eggs on to boil.
Dice celery, green pepper, onion and radishes; shred carrots.
When potatoes are done, rinse with cold water.
Add to sweet relish and other vegetables.
Mix well. Add 7 eggs and mayonnaise; mix.
Slice 3 eggs on top and dust with paprika.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Boil slowly for 5 minutes the first 3 ingredients.
Let cool. Add shortening and mash.
Add flour, soda, vanilla and Sweet 'N Low.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter, vanilla and pecan pieces.
Pour filling into prepared shell (recipe follows). Arrange pecan halves around the inside edge.

title: cheddar garlic biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients well. Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for approximately 15 minutes until golden brown. Makes approximately 10 biscuits.

title: ice cream squares
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ice cream and caramel topping, together.
Put on a cookie sheet and bake at 400°, mixing every 5 minutes.
Put half of mixture into casserole dish.
Top with vanilla ice cream, then pour caramel topping over ice cream; then top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Add sugar, creaming until fluffy. Add eggs and bananas; mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt; stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into well oiled and lightly floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Place pan on rack.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: pickled fish(herring taste)
directions: You may use suckers, Northern or crappies for this recipe.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bones.
Heat soup and broth. Pour over the chicken.
Mix margarine, buttermilk, flour, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: matt's magnificent marinated pork chops
directions: Soak chops overnight in refrigerator.
Grill on open flame for a great taste.

title: my favorite carolina barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir.
Use as a basting sauce for pork or serve with pork barbecue.
Yields 1 quart.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Mix together sour cream, cream cheese, and Uncle Dan's ranch dressing mix.
Refrigerate overnight.
Put crescent roll dough in pan (square, round, etc.) and pinch edges together.
Bake according to directions on tube.
After cooling dough, spread sour cream mixture on top.
Top with sliced, diced, or other veggies. (Very good with broccoli, tomatoes, green peppers, pickles, olives, cauliflower, cucumbers, etc.)

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients, add beaten egg, shortening, orange juice and hot water. Combine only until dry ingredients are moistened. Fold in nuts cranberries and orange rind. Makes 1 loaf. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: honey moist cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, stir together flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients, just until moistened.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Time:
30 minutes.

title: chili hot beans chili recipe
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Lightly brown the meat.
Drain excess fat.
Push to side of pan.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 to 45 min.
Serves 6 to 7 people.

title: fancy potatoes
directions: Mix and let stand at room temperature 1/2 hour.
Put in large baking dish.
Pour 1/2 stick melted butter over top.
Pour crushed potato chips over top.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: baked italian spaghetti
directions: Combine
and
cook until brown.
Salt and pepper.
Make layers of
cooked
spaghetti, meat, olives and grated cheese. Cover with
can
mushroom soup thinned with 1/2 can water. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt and blend 1/3 cup of dry ingredients into butter mixture.
Add nuts. Roll into balls about 1 inch in diameter and put on ungreased sheet.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break bite size pieces of cake in a 22 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan. Beat instant pudding with milk.
Stir in softened ice cream.
Pour over cake.
Set in fridge until firm, about 10 minutes.
Mix jello with hot water.
Add strawberries and pour over cake mixture.
Set in fridge til set.
Frost with Cool Whip.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown meat in small amount of fat.
Add celery and onion.
Cook until light brown.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add chow mein sauce to taste.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: tortilla dessert cups
directions: In a small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon. Coat one side of each tortilla with nonstick cooking spray; sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar. Turn tortillas over; repeat on the other side. Cut each tortilla into 4 wedges. For each dessert cup, place round edge of one tortilla wedge in the bottom of a muffin cup, shaping sides to fit cup. Place a second tortilla wedge in muffin cup, allowing bottom and sides to overlap. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until crisp and lightly browned. Cool completely in pan.

title: meat pie
directions: Brown meat in skillet with seasoning; set aside.
Roll out dough to fit pie plate; fill with ingredients.
Cover with top crust, make opening and flute edges.
Bake at 375° until crust is brown.
Ready to serve.

title: chocolate butter frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients well and beat with mixer.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, blend soup and milk.
Mix in noodles, peas and chicken.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir; top with cheese.
Bake for 5 minutes more or until cheese melts. Serves 4.

title: coffee bars
directions: Combine
oil and sugar; mix well.
Add eggs, coffee and vanilla.
Mix
and sift flour, soda and salt.
Stir into sugar mixture and
mix well.
Spread on greased and floured 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch
jelly
roll pan.
Spread with nuts and chocolate bits on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana popsicles
directions: You will need popsicle sticks or plastic spoons

title: folk's fiddle-faddle
directions: Place popcorn in big bowl.
Put pecans and almonds on a large cookie sheet.
Toast in a 350° oven for 10 minutes to make lightly crisp.

title: plum cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and plums.
Sift together sugar, flour, cinnamon and cloves.
Gradually add dry ingredients to the eggs, oil and plum mixture.
Beat at slow speed for about 2 minutes. Add raisins and nuts.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oatmeal in buttermilk 20 minutes.
Put in bowl and mix with all other ingredients.
You can add nuts, raisins, chocolate chips or chopped fine zucchini, any one of these.
Bake in muffin tins at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Will spring back at finger touch when done.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add all other ingredients and stir lightly; do not overstir.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: chee chee punch
directions: Blend coconut, juice, lemonade and vodka in blender.
Freeze. When ready to serve, dish out in glasses and add 7-Up.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt
sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt over medium heat. Cook
until
mixture
becomes
thick.
Pour
over
cool popcorn. Form into balls. Butter hands or place cool water on hands	(will help
form	balls
more easily).
Place on waxed paper until cool.

title: quick cavatini supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook pasta together according to package instructions.
In a large saucepan, brown ground beef, then drain.
Add sauce, onions, green pepper, mushrooms and pepperoni slices.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes (or longer if time permits).
Rinse pasta in cold water and drain.
Pour into a baking dish.
Pour sauce mixture over pasta.
Mix only slightly. Do not stir.
Cover the top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 15 minutes.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
This recipe makes a lot!
Could be cut in half to serve a family of 3 to 4.

title: bacon crescent appetizer
directions: Beat cream cheese, bacon, parmesan, onion, parsley, and milk in bowl.
Separate dough into 8 rectangles, firmly press perforation together to seal.
Spread each section with 2 Tbsp. cream cheese mixture.
Cut each rectangle into 4 strips and roll end to end.
Place on cookie sheet and brush with egg and water. Bake on 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: marinated salad
directions: Chop these ingredients into small pieces; set aside.

title: punch for a crowd
directions: To boiling water, add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Cool. Mix all ingredients together.
Float ice rings in the punch to help chill.
Serve.

title: shrimp rondeau
directions: Cut smoked shoots into 1-inch lengths.
Soak shoots in cold water for 20 to 30 minutes to soften.
Drain water; rinse shoots in cold water.
Cover with water; boil, uncovered, for 30 to 45 minutes, or until tender.
Add baking soda (substitute for indigenous seasoning).
Add peanut flour or peanut butter; let boil for 1 minute, then simmer for 10 minutes, turning to avoid sticking to the bottom.
Avoid mashing shoots.
Add salt to taste. Tasty with boiled, mashed green bananas.
Also good as a dip with ripe bananas.

title: crab hors d'oeuvres
directions: Melt butter and cheese; add crab meat.
Mix.
Separate muffins and top each with crab mixture.
Sprinkle top with a little Old Bay.
Broil until tops just begin to turn brown.
Cut in quarters and serve.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Finely shred cabbage.
Saute in oil, butter or margarine with sliced onion.
Meanwhile, cook fine egg noodles until done.
Mix together.

title: corn souffle hush puppies
directions: Thaw souffle. Combine flour and next 5 ingredients in bowl. Combine eggs, milk and 3 tablespoons oil. Pour in flour mixture, stirring until blended. Fold in corn souffle. Pour oil 3-inches deep in skillet or big heavy pot. Heat to 370°. Drop batter by tablespoon into hot oil. Fry 3 to 5 minutes or until golden brown. Drain on sacks. Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: spaghetti rice dinner
directions: In large
skillet,
brown ground beef (may add onions). Drain. Add
rice, spaghetti sauce mix and tomatoes. Stir until mixed. Add
water;
bring to a boil, then simmer for approximately 20 minutes until rice is done.

title: refried bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn chips in small pan.
Cook over low heat, stirring until heated.
Keep warm in chafing dish. Serve with corn chips.
Makes approximately 3 cups.

title: really quick wheat bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then blend milk with egg.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Stir and pour batter into greased loaf pan, dusted with wheat germ.
Sprinkle wheat germ on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let loaf rest 10 minutes in loaf pan, turn out and brush loaf with honey.

title: busy day pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Brown on stove ground beef, garlic, onion, salt and pepper.
Add tomato sauce, carrots and peas. Cover top with mashed potatoes.
Bake in large casserole for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: the best cheese cake
directions: Make or buy a graham cracker crust for a 9-inch cake.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream sugar and cheese thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, until blended.
Add vanilla and sour cream and beat thoroughly for at least 5 minutes.
Bake in a 9-inch spring-form pan for 45 minutes.
Turn off heat and leave in oven for 1 hour. Do not open oven.
Let cool, then chill for several hours before serving.
Enjoy!

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Place with bread crumbs in bottom of 11 x 14-inch baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over sausage.
Cook at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Can be frozen.
If so, cook only 30 minutes, then when thawed, cook 15 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Make into small balls. Bake on cookie sheet at 425° for about 18 minutes. These can be frozen and reheated.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well, make into loaf.
Cover with catsup or tomato sauce. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Turn oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and beat until peaks form.
Add vanilla and salt. Gently, fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Place small teaspoon of dough on foil.
Place in oven.
Turn oven off.
Leave cookies in oven overnight.

title: orange chicken
directions: Skin chicken breasts.
Salt chicken and coat in flour.
Melt margarine in heavy iron skillet.
Add chicken to melted margarine and brown.
Pour orange juice over chicken and cook on low until done.
Chicken is very tender, has a wonderful flavor and will practically "fall off the bone."
Serve with herb rice.
Be sure to cover the chicken while cooking on low.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325°
for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with chocolate chips just before putting into oven.

title: apple pie
directions: Cook apples and water and stir in remaining ingredients.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Heat vegetable oil in pan. Mix egg and milk. Dip sliced tomatoes in egg mixture, then in flour or cornmeal. Place in frying pan. Brown on both sides. Serve hot.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
When well coated, put into greased tube pan.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Set aside. In large mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla extract or orange peel until creamy. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in oats and Nestle Toll House butterscotch flavored morsels. Drop by measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 7 to 8 minutes for chewier cookies, 9 to 10 minutes for crisper cookies. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and dry mustard.
Layer bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour milk mixture over.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves approximately 8.

title: black bean quesadillas
directions: Slightly mash black beans with a fork in small bowl.
Stir in green onion, bell pepper, onion, lime juice, cilantro and garlic. Set aside.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Trim all fat from chops.
Beat egg white with milk.
Place chops in milk mixture.
Let stand for 5 minutes, turning chops once.
Mix together cornflake crumbs, bread crumbs and Season-All. Remove chops from mixture.
Coat thoroughly with crumb mixture. Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with nonstick spray coating.
Place chops in pan and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Turn chops, bake 20 minutes longer.

title: joan's coconut pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into slightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon oat lacies
directions: Lightly dust cookie sheets with flour to prevent burning.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with fresh vegies.

title: rosy apple punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot apple juice in large punch bowl.
Add cold apple juice and lemon juice; mix well.
Stir in ginger ale just before serving.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press out rolls in a pizza pan (or big, round pan).
Sprinkle sausage on top of rolls.
Combine remaining ingredients together; pour on top of sausage.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Place sweet potatoes in buttered 9 x 13 pan.
Cover with apples and then marshmallows.
Mix cornstarch with water and pour over everything.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with pecans.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 375° until potatoes are tender, about one hour.

title: claudia berrier's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together and place in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until well done, about 1 hour.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and beat for 2 minutes.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: j. b.'s sad cake
directions: Grease and flour a large loaf pan (at least a 2-quart pan). Combine all ingredients and bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and let simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine beef, egg, celery, onion, crackers and salt and pepper.
Shape into 6 patties.
Brown quickly in hot skillet. Place in shallow baking dish, 7 x 9-inch.

title: karmel-nut korn
directions: Divide popcorn and nuts between 2 ungreased rectangular pans (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Cook brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until bubbly around edges.
Continue cooking 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda until foamy.
Pour over popcorn and nuts, stirring until popcorn is well coated.
Bake uncovered in 200° oven, stirring every 15 minutes for 1 hour.
Yields 15 servings.

title: german pancake(dutch babies)
directions: Butter a heavy 10-inch ovenproof skillet.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Blend eggs, salt and flour.
Add milk and mix thoroughly. Pour into pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°; reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes more.
Serve with powdered sugar and heated maple syrup.

title: pot roast
directions: Put roast in pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover and bake at approximately 325° until tender or for about 4 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: herbed biscuits
directions: In small bowl, beat mustard and milk together.
In a large bowl, combine biscuit mix, spices and chives.
Pour in milk-mustard mixture.
Stir.
Do not overbeat.
Roll out 3/4-inch thick.
Cut into 2-inch rounds, using biscuit cutter.
Bake 12 minutes at 450° until done.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: In a saucepan mix sugar, white vinegar, water, green pepper and pimiento.
Add salt.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and cold water.
Add to hot mixture.
Cook and stir until sauce thickens and bubbles.
Cool.
Add paprika.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: texas chili
directions: In a large heavy pan, heat oil and brown beef cubes on all sides.
Add onions, bell pepper and garlic and fry with beef for about 5 minutes.
Add all the remaining ingredients except beans and simmer chili for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add beans and simmer 30 minutes more.
Serve.
Sprinkle with cheese of choice.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: In large crock-pot, put barbecue sauce and apricot preserves. Make small meatballs with hamburger mixed with chopped onions. Saute meatballs in cooking oil until brown on all sides.
Pour your meatballs into barbecue and preserve mixture.
Turn to low heat. Cook for 3 or 4 hours.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to boil for 1 minute.
Add 1/2 cup peanut butter and 3 cups oatmeal.
Stir; spoon or pour into pan.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Place onions in baking dish.
Pour melted butter over onions. Add rice, beef broth and consomme.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(An old South Carolina recipe.)

title: eggplant lasagna
directions: Slice eggplant thinly.
Combine oil with herbs and brush both sides of eggplant.
Brown both sides of eggplant until tender. Layer half of the eggplant slices, Mozzarella, Ricotta, spaghetti sauce, fennel seed and olives (in that order).
Repeat layering. Top with remaining Mozzarella and garnish with sliced olives. Cover and bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Let stand 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, then chocolate.

title: strawberry cookies
directions: Mix milk, coconut and 1 package gelatin mix. Shape into strawberry shapes and roll into second package of dry gelatin mix. Place on waxed paper. Pipe on a cap and stem of green frosting. Great for dressing up a cookie tray.

title: cheesy squares
directions: Mix butter, cake mix and 1 egg; pat down in a 9x13 inch pan like a crust. Mix cream cheese and 2 eggs; gradually add powdered sugar.
Pour over crust; sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: yankee cornbread
directions: Mix and stir together flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg, milk, cream-style corn and oil; add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: grilled turkey(very moist)
directions: You will need syringe and needle (can purchase at any pharmacy).

title: batter white bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast on water, stir in until dissolved.
Add 3 1/4 cups flour, sugar, salt and shortening. Blend on low speed, then 2 minutes at medium speed.
Beat in 3 1/4 cups flour by hand. Cover, let stand 45 minutes.
Stir hard 1/2 minute.
Spread in 2 greased bread pans.
Let rise 20 minutes.
Bake at 365° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix corn, green beans, onion, green pepper, celery, sour cream, 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and cream of celery soup.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Melt margarine.
Stir in crackers and 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: walnut squares
directions: Beat egg until foamy.
Then beat in vanilla and sift and stir in flour, salt and soda.
Mix in nuts.
Spread in well greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine the margarine, oats, sugar, flour, and vanilla in a bowl and mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 12 minutes. Makes 24.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs; add to creamed mixture and add Karo and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together; add to butter mixture.
Add rest of ingredients.
Make into 4 rolls and place in refrigerator.
Chill 24 hours; slice 1/4-inch thick and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach; drain.
Place in casserole dish evenly.
Add bacon and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° until heated throughout. Spread sour cream over; sprinkle cheese on top.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: rotini and vegetables(international:  italy)
directions: Heat oil.
Saute next 7 ingredients slowly for 10 minutes. Add cooked, drained rotini to vegetables.
Heat through.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: chewy chocolate and chip cookies
directions: *Half of each kind of chip is very good.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in baking dish.
Cover with onion mix, apricots and dressing.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Uncover last 5 minutes.
Bake at 350°.

title: pecan pie(serves 6 to 12)
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter.
Spread nuts in bottom of shell; pour in filling.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°, then 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mrs. williams pound cake
directions: Beat eggs
in
mixer
until
well
blended.
Add sugar, melted butter,
Crisco and flour.	Gradually add milk and beat well.
Add yellow coloring and continue to beat.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: pecan logs
directions: Mix sugar, coconut, pecans, vanilla, cracker crumbs, butter and peanut butter together.
Make into small logs.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler. Dip logs into chocolate. Lay on wax paper until cold.

title: parmesan snack crackers
directions: In a 2-quart casserole or bowl, place margarine.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 1 1/2 to 3 minutes or until melted.
Stir in Parmesan cheese, celery salt, paprika and garlic or onion powder.
Add crackers, then toss until coated.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 3 minutes, stirring after every minute. Then spread on paper towels to cool.
Transfer to a tightly covered container.
Store at room temperature for up to 1 week. Makes 10 servings (1/2 cup).

title: scandinavian rye bread
directions: Choose mixing and kneading method, except food processor.
Add butter and salt to Rye Sponge.
Add all-purpose flour as specified.
Knead.
Let dough rise 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: baker's cream filling
directions: Blend milk and flour until smooth.
Cook over medium heat until it becomes thick paste.
Pour over butter, shortening, salt and sugar.
Stir together.
Add vanilla and stir.
Chill in freezer until well chilled.
Remove from freezer and beat on medium, then high until whipped.

title: strawberry julius
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and mix well.
You can also use orange juice in place of the strawberries for an orange julius.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, cornmeal, sugar, 1/2 cup butter, eggs, salt and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth. Stir in enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
(Dough is ready if indentation remains when touched.)

title: jello popcorn balls
directions: Boil syrup, sugar and jello for 1 minute.
Pour over popcorn. Form into balls.

title: bob andy pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4. In a large mixing bowl, combine sugars, flour, cinnamon, cloves and salt. In another bowl beat the eggs, add milk, butter and vanilla. Stir wet ingredients into the dry ingredients then pour into the pie crust. Bake for 45 minutes. The filling will be shaky when you remove it from the oven. The pie puffs up, but levels off as it cools. Serve at room temperature. Serves 8-10.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix margarine and cheese well. Add 1 cup sugar at a time. Add one egg at a time.
Fold in flour one cup at a time.
Add vanilla.
Put in cold oven set at 300°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours. Do not open oven door while baking.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half, lengthwise.
Remove yolks.
Mash yolks with a fork.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Stuff the whites with the yolk mixture.
Garnish with paprika and parsley.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill overnight.
Serve with carrots, celery, cucumbers, broccoli, cauliflower or potato chips.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake as directed on box.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar together.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 cup sugar.
Mix well and spread on cool pretzel crust.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix eggs, hamburger meat, salt, pepper, garlic powder and corn flakes.
Then roll into small balls and bake until done.
Then heat until smooth the jelly, catsup, cloves and red wine vinegar. Add meatballs and simmer for long time.

title: brenda tapley's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix all other ingredients except crackers, oleo and enough cheese to layer top.
Pour into greased casserole.
Mix remaining cheese and cracker crumbs in melted oleo.
Sprinkle on top of macaroni.
Bake at 350° until bubbly or lightly browned.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: This recipe may be doubled.

title: confetti rice
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove to paper towels.
Add rice, carrots, celery and peas; cook until heated through, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir in bacon.
Serve with soy sauce, if desired.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Blend and mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in greased and floured long pan.

title: fig preserves
directions: Wash figs and cut off stems.
Place in a 4 qt. pan.
Do NOT add water.
Pour sugar over figs.
Add orange rind.
Cook one hour very slowly with lid on.
Stir occasionally.
Cook two more hours or until juice is dark and thick.
Spoon figs and juice into jars that have been sterilized in boiling water.
Place lid and band on jar and screw tight.

title: italiano vegetables
directions: In a large skillet or Dutch oven, combine all ingredients, except olives.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes, until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Cool slightly.
Add olives.
Transfer to bowl.
Cover.
Chill 6 hours or overnight. Makes about 9 cups.

title: best brownies
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat well with spoon.
Combine dry ingredients and gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake at 350° until edges come away from side of pan and toothpick in middle comes clean.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix egg, sour cream, butter and cornbread mix.
Add corn and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In saucepan, bring chicken broth, onion, bay leaf, dash of garlic and broccoli to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until tender.
Remove bay leaf. Add butter, salt and pepper.
Mix flour and milk together, then add to soup.
Stir and heat until thickened. Serve.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift flour; add shortening and cheese.
Mix together.
Add buttermilk and knead together.
Turn dough on a lightly floured surface and knead together.
Roll dough out about 1/2 inch thick. Cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 425° for about 12 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: artichoke chips
directions: Slice the artichokes into chips as thinly as possible.
Rinse the chips under cold water; pat dry.
Deep fry them in several batches in hot, but not smoking, oil in a skillet until a pale golden color.
Drain; change the oil and briefly fry them again to a crisp golden brown.
Drain each completed batch on a baking sheet lined with paper towel and keep warm in a low oven while you finish the remaining chips.
Season generously with sea salt and serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: antipasto
directions: Boil carrots and fennel bulb about 3 minutes then plunge in ice water.
Remove skin and slice peppers.
Toss together.

title: meat loaf hot dish
directions: Make your favorite meat loaf, using very ground beef.
Pat in bottom of casserole.

title: fresh crab salad
directions: Combine
all ingredients, except lettuce.
Stir to mix. Cover and chill
1 to 2 hours.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Yields 4 servings.

title: freezer white bread
directions: Spoon flour into measuring cup and level off; pour onto waxed paper.
Combine 4 cups flour, undissolved yeast, dry milk, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Stir well to blend; add oleo, then add hot tap water.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes with electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 2 cups more flour; beat at high speed for 2 minutes or until thick and elastic.
Gradually stir in just enough remaining flour with a wooden spoon to make a soft dough which leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out on floured board. Knead 10 minutes or until dough is smooth and elastic.
Cover with plastic wrap, then a towel.
Let rest 15 minutes on board.
Punch down, divide dough into 4 equal parts, shape each part into a ball and flatten into 7-inch circles or shape into loaves.
Wrap tightly in plastic wrap and place circles on baking sheets and loaves in pans.
Freeze until firm.
Wrap plastic wrapped frozen dough in aluminum foil.
Freezer dough is best if it is baked within 4 weeks of freezing.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Place in dish.
Layer the rest of ingredients in order given.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread over top as you would frosting.
Top with grated cheese. Cover and refrigerate 8 to 10 hours.
Garnish with bacon.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake cake mix using directions for 9 x 13-inch pan.
In saucepan, combine 1 cup milk, 1 cup sugar and marshmallows.
Cook until marshmallows are melted.
Stir in coconut.
Pour over hot cake.
In saucepan, combine 2 cups sugar, 1/2 cup milk, cocoa and margarine.
Bring to boil.
Stirring constantly, boil
3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour over cake.

title: stuffed pepper soup
directions: Saute green peppers, onion and celery in 1 tablespoon oil or use water or broth, about 1/4 cup.
Combine tomatoes, juice and well-drained sauteed vegetables in soup kettle.
Saute ground meat and drain well.
Combine with vegetables in kettle.
Add rice and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour and oats.
Blend with mixer until coarse crumbs.
Press into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread melted chips.

title: biscotti di prato(the dunking cookie)
directions: To toast almonds, bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put pineapple, including juice, in a large bowl.
Add mandarin oranges, fruit cocktail and chopped apple.
Mix well, then add dry pudding mix.
After mixing carefully, put in refrigerator overnight until ready to serve.
Before serving, add bananas and 1/3 of an 8 ounce carton of Cool Whip.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and stem berries. About 1 hour before serving, pour berries in pie shell. Cover with confectioners sugar. Whip the cream with sugar and vanilla; spread on top of pie.
Chill until ready to serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stay-a-bed stew
directions: Place in a large casserole dish, cover and cook at 275° for 5 hours.
Remove bay leaf and enjoy.

title: tenderloin tips
directions: Put meat in bottom of a casserole dish. Sprinkle on dry onion soup mix.
Pour on the soup and wine vinegar.
Cover and bake at 250° for 3 hours. Do not peek, do not stir.

title: cabbage a la creme
directions: Cut cabbage into thin slices; boil for 8 minutes in small amount of boiling salted water.
Drain; stir in milk and margarine.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 large servings.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Next add egg yolks and beat slightly. Add other ingredients and pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix the first five ingredients, then add the rest of the ingredients except the confectioners sugar. Beat until just combined.
Bake for 1 hour or until top springs back when lightly pressed with fingertips.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and serve.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground meat. Drain. Season with salt and pepper. Add beans, tomatoes, paste, water and seasoning. When serving, pour over cooked rice and garnish with crackers.

title: spicy beef dip
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic in skillet until meat is lightly brown and onion is tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, catsup, sugar and oregano leaves.
Simmer gently for 10 minutes.
Spoon off excess fat.
Remove from heat.
Add cream cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Heat and stir until cream cheese is melted and well blended.
Keep warm in chafing dish or buffet server.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: raisin "depression" cake
directions: Notice:
No eggs or milk (or butter if you used lard).

title: green beans
directions: Cut and brown the bacon; drain.
Drain green beans.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths and coat with sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes in a 1-quart casserole dish. Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbles.

title: bean salad
directions: Cook lima beans until still firm.
Make a dressing of the salt, pepper, seasoning, oil and vinegar.
Combine all ingredients with the dressing.
Chill and serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in oven at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: surprise dessert
directions: Combine crackers and margarine.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat pudding, milk and ice cream with mixer and pour over crust. Top with
whipped topping. Store in refrigerator.

title: diana's holiday punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat; add juices and almond extract.
Freeze.
Just before serving, put frozen punch in bowl and add ginger ale. Garnish with apple slices.
For decorative touch, cut a star shape from apple slices with a small cookie cutter.
Makes about 70 (4 ounce) servings.

title: ham and turkey roll-ups
directions: Use baked ham topped with turkey and then cooked asparagus. Roll up and place on a buttered baking dish.
Cover and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
When ready to serve, spoon cheese sauce over top.
This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: chestnut pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar slowly.
Melt butter. Fold in butter and cream.
Add flour and vanilla.
Bake in unbaked pie shell for 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake an additional 35 minutes.

title: sugarless cinnamon cookies
directions: Combine margarine and vanilla.
Cream together until light and fluffy.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add flour mixture, 1/4 cup at a time, into margarine.
Combine sugar substitute and orange juice; stir into flour mixture.
Mix well. Sprinkle cinnamon over dough; knead to make a streaked appearance. Shape dough into balls about 1/2 inch in diameter; arrange on a nonstick cookie sheet.
Flatten the balls with a fork dipped in cold water.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: green salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in hot water, add cut marshmallows and stir until marshmallows melt.
When this mixture begins to congeal, add pineapple, nuts and whipped cream.
Mold.
Serve on lettuce with cream cheese and mayonnaise.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in punch bowl.

title: seismic salsa
directions: Process first 10 ingredients.
In large bowl, combine them with last 6 ingredients.
If too thick for your taste, add some canned plum tomatoes and juice.
Scoop with your favorite tortilla chips.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown sausage, beef and onions.
Drain.
Add paste, sauce and tomatoes.
Simmer.
Mix three cheeses together.
Layer noodles, meat sauce and cheese until all is used.
Bake until cheese is melted.
Makes two 11 x 13-inch pans.
Makes 2 layers each.

title: southern fried corn
directions: Shuck corn; wash.
Cut the kernels off the cob with a sharp knife.
Scrape the juice out of the corn cob into the corn.
Heat the drippings or margarine in a large skillet.
Add the corn, flour, sugar, water, milk and seasonings.
Stir together, bringing mixture to a boil.
Stir the corn constantly until it starts to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer until corn is tender, about 25 to 30 minutes.
If necessary, add more water and more sugar (1/4 cup).

title: farmer's brownies
directions: Mix cocoa in hot water.
Stir margarine into this.
Allow to cool.
Stir dry ingredients into cocoa mixture.
Add eggs.
Beat in milk and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Put in a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage bread(weight watchers)
directions: Heat margarine and oil over medium heat until bubbly.
Add garlic; saute until golden, about 1 minute.
Press dough into a 17 x 10-inch rectangle sheet.
Brush dough with half of the garlic mixture.
Arrange Provolone over dough.
Top with sausage. Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Firmly press into dough, starting from wide end.
Roll, jelly roll fashion.
Pinch to enclose and pinch ends.
Put, seam sides down, onto nonstick sheet.
Brush with remaining garlic
mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.
(If bread is browning too quickly, cover with foil.) Cool 15 minutes and slice.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water; cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Beat in flour mixture, alternately with buttermilk.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Pour batter into 3 (9-inch) layer pans lined on bottoms with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb punch
directions: Cut rhubarb into 1-inch pieces.
Add water to cover.
Cook until soft, about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Makes 3 quarts of juice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Combine mixtures.
Stir to coat evenly.
Refrigerate for about 3 hours.
Toss again before serving.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 1 3/4-quart casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.
If dried out, add more margarine.

title: graham cookies
directions: Place graham crackers in raised edge cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Melt sugar and margarine; boil for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Pour over crackers and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool and break each cracker where perforated.

title: coconut chews
directions: Pat brown sugar and shortening into a pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Add eggs, Karo, vanilla, flour, baking powder, coconut and nuts together.
Bake 25 minutes longer at 350°.

title: sedalia's louisiana gumbo(fourth generation recipe)
directions: You will need 1 large heavy pot (approximately 20 quarts).

title: martha's dish
directions: Saute round steak in butter.
Layer raw cut-up bacon, sauteed steak and sliced onion.
Mix tomato sauce, garlic cloves, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Spread over layered ingredients.
Cover with can of kidney beans.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve on rice.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Put flour and salt in a pie plate.
Mix oil and milk in a cup and pour into pie plate.
Mix with flour and salt and press in plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and softened margarine.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Cream sugar and cream cheese; spread over crust.
Spread Cool Whip over this and chill.

title: southwest chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Layer chicken, onion, chilies, cheese, sour cream and corn in pan.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream
the
shortening	and
sugar, then add eggs. Sift flour and soda together. Add with potato chips to egg mixture. Add butterscotch
bits	and
vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased
cookie
sheet.
Bake
at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 8 dozen.

title: yummy chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk.
Heat on medium until boiling point. Add butter and stir.
Let boil without stirring for 4 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: grandpa mcmurry's fat-free beans
directions: Cook bacon and pat dry to remove as much fat as possible. Combine the ingredients and cook until beans are tender.
Add water as needed.

title: belgian pate
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate 1 day before serving with party rye bread or crackers.

title: chicken and carrot salad
directions: Combine lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Toss all ingredients together and add to mayonnaise/lemon juice dressing.
Chill and serve on lettuce.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until soft.
Drain and cool well.
Add hard-boiled eggs, onion, sugar, mustard, vinegar, mayonnaise or salad dressing and salt and pepper to taste.
Carrots and celery are good with it.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together. Store in airtight container.
A mug and this mixture will make a nice gift.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Remove stems and some of meat.
Chop and saute stems with onions in 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in all else, except cheese and rest of butter and wine.
Melt butter and coat mushrooms with it.
Fill each mushroom with stuffing and pile cheese on top.
Pour wine into baking pan and bake mushrooms at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Chop onion, garlic, pickles, olives and pimentos.
Add mayonnaise, oil, vinegar, lemon juice and parsley flakes.
Mix well.
Put in jar and let stand overnight before using.
Will keep 3 to 4 weeks.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Melt Cheez Whiz in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix hominy, green chilies and soup.
Add cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french fried cream casserole
directions: Line bottom of a 2-quart casserole with butter chunks.
Pour bag of fries on top.
Sprinkle with minced onion, salt and pepper. Cover with whipping cream and sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Not recommended for cooking ahead and/or freezing.
Simple and delicious.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese ball(from ora's kitchen)
directions: I grate the cheese and let it stand until it is room temperature.
Mix well and form into ball. Roll in chopped pecans and chili powder.

title: pear honey
directions: *BLKLIN life through Jesus Christ our Lord."
Romans 6:23

title: marsha's lasagna
directions: Cook together meat, onion, garlic, salt and pepper until brown.
Add oil and oleo to water and boil noodles.
After meat is brown; drain and add tomatoes, sauce, paste, basil, salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat for 20 minutes.

title: rice dish
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir to mix; place mixture in a baking dish or pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan squares
directions: Blend all ingredients until moistened.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: steak diane
directions: Heat margarine and Worcestershire in large nonstick skillet until hot.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Saute until tender.
Pound steaks to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread 1 1/2 teaspoons mustard on one side of each steak.
Push mushrooms to one side of skillet; add steaks, mustard side down.
Cook steaks 3 to 4 minutes over medium heat.
Spread remaining mustard on top side of steaks. Flip and cook 3 to 4 minutes on second side or until done as you like.
Lightly pierce steaks in several places with fork.
Top with brandy; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Serve on heated plates, topped with mushrooms.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix butter, milk and powdered sugar. Add coconut and pecans, then knead in 1 pound powdered sugar. Roll in balls and freeze overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour; add water.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture thickens and comes to a boil; blend in cheese.
Combine sauce, broccoli and eggs; mix gently until blended.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart ovenproof casserole and cover with crumbs.
Dot with remaining butter. Place casserole on cooking grill (or in a 350° oven) and cook for 30 minutes.

title: breaded round steak and onions
directions: Blend flour and spices.
Dip steak strips in flour; dip in egg mixture and flour mixture again.
Lightly brown steak in skillet on medium heat.
Place browned steak in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook onions in remaining oil until clear.
Set onions over steak; add 1/2 cup water.
Tightly seal with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours. Don't peek, the onions and steam make the steak fork-tender. Leftover steak make great sandwiches.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups water (boiling) over dates; let stand until lukewarm.
add egg, butter, nuts and vanilla.
Sift together sugar, salt, baking soda, flour and baking powder.
Add sifted mixture to dates; mix until well blended.
Use 2 loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugars, butter and oil together.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Add dry ingredients to mixture.
Shape into balls using a teaspoonful of dough for each ball.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten each ball with bottom of a glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy strawberry cake
directions: Mix and cook as directed on box.
Make 2 layers.
Cut cake layers into 4 layers when cool.

title: beet relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl, then blend well.
Chill thoroughly.
Relish keeps well stored in refrigerator for about a week.

title: meat and cheese stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells in boiling water according to directions on box. In a frying pan, brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Drain off any extra grease.
Add bread crumbs and parsley; set aside.
Cover bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with 2/3 cup of spaghetti sauce.
After shells are cool, fill with meat mixture and place in baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over the shells until they are completely covered.
Sprinkle grated cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters, reserving 1/3 cup liquid.
Combine crumbs, butter, salt, pepper, celery and parsley.
Spread third of crumbs in 8 x 1 1/2-inch round pan.
Cover with half the oysters.
Using another third of the crumbs, spread a second layer; cover with remaining oysters.
Combine milk and oyster liquid and pour over oysters.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 40 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Cook wide egg noodles; drain.
Mix meat, onion, pepper and celery; add alternately with noodles to casserole dish.
Mix soups together; pour over the layers.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° until bubbly, or for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Add cold water to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened.
Stir in whipped topping with whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Stir in oranges and pineapple, marshmallows and coconut.
Spoon in 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix and chill until partially congealed the jello, boiling water, sugar and pineapple
Fold in Dream Whip, chopped pecans and Cheddar cheese.
Chill until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli and place in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Grate cheese and mix with soup and onion flakes and pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, layer potatoes, ham and onion and soup mixture.
Repeat.
Add pepper, if desired.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese before baking.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter or margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well until lemon colored.
Combine flour, baking powder and milk.
Add flavoring.
Beat well.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: baked lasagne casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with oil, onion, garlic and parsley. Add tomato paste, water, salt and pepper (for hot lasagne, add 1 can Ro-Tel also); simmer 30 minutes.

title: ruby's lemon-strawberry punch
directions: Combine lemonade and strawberries.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Makes about 1 1/2 gallons or 32 half-cup servings.

title: one layer banana pudding
directions: Cook until thick.
Pour over wafers and bananas.

title: parmesan and herb biscuits
directions: Let bread dough thaw and rise as directed on package, except grease 2 layer pans, 8 or 9 x 1 1/2-inch.
Shape each loaf into 18 balls.
Dip the balls into 2 tablespoons butter, then dip tops into cheese. Arrange in one pan.
Arrange remaining balls in the other pan.
Mix dill weed, salt and 2 tablespoons butter. Brush dill mixture on rolls in second pan. Sprinkle with parsley flakes. Cover and let rise about 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden.
Makes 3 dozen rolls.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling salt water for 5 minutes and drain.
Stir in carrots.
Combine stuffing and butter.
Spread half of stuffing in baking dish and spoon vegetables on top. Sprinkle remaining stuffing on vegetables.
Bake at 350 for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, pudding mix and flour.
Add eggs, oil and water and then mix together in a small bowl sugar and cinnamon.

title: deviled ham and cheese ball
directions: Garnish Ideas:
Can roll in 1/2 cup chopped nuts (almonds or pecans), or radish slices or pimiento.

title: lone star pork chop skillet
directions: Sprinkle both sides of chops with cumin and salt. Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat. Brown chops on both sides, about 2 to 3 minutes per side. Remove and reserve. Reduce heat. Add garlic and onion to skillet; add chops, simmer uncovered 10 to 12 minutes, turning chops after 5 minutes. Remove chops to serving plate; keep warm. Add tomatoes and picante sauce to skillet to make sauce. Cook sauce over high heat until thickened, 1 to 2 minutes. Arrange chops over rice. Spoon sauce over rice; sprinkle with cilantro. Serve with additional picante sauce.

title: communion bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put all ingredients in bowl.
Mix by hand as pie crust.
Roll dough.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet. Cut into strips.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until slightly brown.
When done, part strips.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix onion, Bisquick, eggs, oil, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add zucchini, blending well.
Pour into buttered 3 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together meats, eggs, onion, crumbs, salt and pepper. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Put on cookie sheet and bake in 350° to 375° oven until browned.
Mix soups together in large casserole dish.
Add browned meatballs.
Put in refrigerator and marinate all day or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Tear cake into small pieces and place in a large bowl.
In another bowl, mix sour cream, evaporated milk, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Fold this mixture into torn cake.
Place in a glass bowl.
Mix glaze with sliced strawberries. Place on top of cake mixture.
Cover and chill.
Keeps well.

title: olive's candied apples
directions: Peel apples and quarter.
Place in heavy pan or iron skillet. Add sugar on top of apples.
Stir so each piece will be coated with sugar.
Then add water and stir with wooden spoon or hands.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Saute pecans in butter until golden brown.
Cool.
Beat eggs at medium speed until frothy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until thick.
Stir in next two ingredients.
Pour mixture in freezer can of 4 or 5 quart freezer.
Add enough milk to reach fill line. Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Let ripen at least 1 hour.
Yield:
about 1 gallon.

title: ship wreck
directions: Make in layers in a casserole dish or pan in order of ingredients.
Use amounts according to size of dish.
Season with salt and pepper as you go along.
Bake for 2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook hash brown potatoes.
Add margarine.
Put in bottom of pan.
Pour can of cream of chicken soup with remainder of ingredients.

title: helen's chicken wings
directions: Combine and simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour over wings.
Marinate for 24 hours.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Enough for 14 wings.

title: quick caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in a large mixing bowl; set aside.
Combine butter and brown sugar in a 1-cup glass measure.
Microwave on High, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, or until mixture has boiled 1 minute, stirring once or twice.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Pour syrup mixture over popped corn.
Toss to evenly coat corn.
If desired, shape into balls or spread on waxed paper until cool and dry.

title: pecan dainties
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla together.
Sir in flour and pecans.
Chill.
Shape into marble size balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes until firm, but not brown.
Roll gently in powdered sugar.
Cool.
Sugar again. Makes 50 cookies.

title: enchilada casserole(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9
x 13-inch baking dish lightly.
Brown ground beef and drain, then return to heat; add onion and cook for about 5 minutes.
Then add salt, pepper, garlic and cumin.
Add soups, chilies and enchilada sauce.
Mix together; set aside.
Cut tortillas in quarters; put in bottom of baking dish.
Cover with 1/2 of meat mixture; layer another layer of tortillas and meat mixture.
Cover with grated cheese and bake 30 minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll thawed bread into a rectangle.
Spread with brown mustard. Sprinkle with oregano and garlic powder.
Layer ham, hard salami, Provolone cheese and diced onion.
Fold into thirds; seal and brush with egg.
Spray aluminum foil-lined cookie sheet with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until dough is brown.

title: southern smothered pork chops
directions: This recipe appeared on a postcard that I bought in the South. It is an old recipe without specific measurements, so the ingredients are prepared to taste and the number of servings.

title: light batter
directions: In bowl stir together 5 ingredients.
Add water and egg; stir until smooth.
Pour 1 qt. (about) corn oil into large skillet to depth of 1/2 inch, filling no more than 1/3 full.
Heat over medium heat to 375°.
Dip 4 cups cut up vegetables,
1 lb boneless chicken 13 breasts cut into in cubes a few pieces at a time.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes turning once until brown and crisp. Drain on paper towels.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: In large bowl, combine chicken, drained pineapple and drained peas.
Mix yogurt with mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour over macaroni mixture and stir until well coated.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans and serve.

title: curried hot fruit
directions: Place ingredients in pan and cook in a 325° oven to melt. Drain pineapple, pears, apricots, peaches and dark cherries.
Add to pan; stir well.
Bake one hour in a 325° oven.

title: steamed rice
directions: Butter a baking dish (2-quart).
Put all ingredients in and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Serves six.
(May be doubled.)

title: cap'n crunch mix
directions: Mix and drop in clusters on waxed paper.

title: mexican sweet bread
directions: Be sure to get hot roll mix with yeast packet.
In a bowl, mix roll yeast.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Prepare dough according to package.
Divide into pieces.
Pat each into 2 1/2 inches around.
Place on baking sheet.
Let rise.

title: unfried french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice each potato as you like for fries.
Coat baking (cookie) sheet with 3 sprays of vegetable oil (Pam).
Combine egg whites and the Cajun spice in a bowl; beat. Add potatoes.
Mix well.
Put potatoes on baking sheet, adding liquid off them.
Leave space between each.
(I use 2 cookie sheets.)
Place shelves at lowest position in oven.
Turn every 8 minutes for about 45 to 60 minutes.
Let them brown evenly.
These have only the calories of baked potatoes because they have no fats!

title: oven potatoes
directions: Mix flour and cheese together.
Melt butter in long baking dish.
Roll potatoes in flour and cheese mix.
Place in baking dish.
Roll over in margarine.
Sprinkle hamburger seasoning salt over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn potatoes over and sprinkle hamburger seasoning salt over them.
Bake for 30 more minutes.

title: sour cream twists
directions: Place in warm bowl the warm water.
Sprinkle or crumble in yeast; stir until yeast is completely dissolved.
Combine in another bowl the flour, melted butter, sour cream, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add dissolved yeast.
Mix until well blended.
Cover with damp cloth.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Stir down.
Combine 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Mix well.
Sprinkle evenly over breadboard.
Roll dough out on board to 15 x 18-inch rectangle.
Turn dough to coat both sides.
Fold dough in thirds.
Roll out again in rectangle 1/4-inch thick.
Use all the cinnamon/sugar mix.
Cut dough into 1 x 4-inch strips.
Twist.
Place on greased sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes until done.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: sausage and potato casserole
directions: Take 1/2 of sausage and pat into dish; layer with sliced potatoes and cheese.
Pat the remaining sausage on top of cheese; layer with potatoes and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 325°, or uncover until cheese has browned.

title: oven stew
directions: Place pieces of kielbasa in a skillet with 1/2 cup chopped scallions.
Add 1 cup water and enough red wine to cover them and cook until kielbasa are heated.
Remove them and cook down the wine a bit.
Then spoon the sauce over the kielbasa.

title: steamed chicken and gravy
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and cook in 1/4-inch of hot oil until lightly brown.
Place chicken in a large Dutch oven. Add water and butter.
Cook, covered, over medium heat for 40 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken to serving platter. Reserve pan drippings.
Combine flour and 1/4 cup water until smooth.
Pour flour mixture into pan drippings.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Serve gravy with chicken.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread dry cake mix over filling.
