Dot margarine over top.
Sprinkle nuts over all. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: slim-but-saucy pot roast
directions: Brown roast. Place in crock-pot; cover with potatoes, carrots, onions and all other ingredients. Cook on low all day.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Peel peaches using as many as syrup will cover.
Make syrup by mixing vinegar, sugar, cinnamon and cloves, boiling until rather thick.
Add peeled peaches, one at a time.
Cook until tender, not mushy.
Remove fruit from syrup and place in sterilized jars.
Boil syrup until thick; pour over peaches filling jars to top seal.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bring to a boil in a saucepan water and butter.
Add next 6 ingredients to water, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick. Pour into browned pie shell.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Boil water; add butter and melt.
Add lobster meat.
Simmer. Add flour, a little at a time.
Add milk, while stirring fast. Add seasonings and keep stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat and add sherry.

title: spinach dip
directions: Defrost and drain spinach.
Pull apart and chop fine.
Add mayonnaise, sour cream, vegetable soup, chestnuts and onion; mix well and refrigerate.

title: sour cream almond fruit cake
directions: You will need cheesecloth.

title: tuna cheese spread
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature for about 1 hour. Drain tuna; mash with fork.
In medium bowl, combine cream cheese, tuna and mayonnaise.
Add lemon juice, curry and salt.
Mix to blend well.
Add onions and stir to blend.
Chill for 1 hour for flavors to blend.
Serve with crackers, radishes, carrot or celery.
Can be used as a dip.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: miracle soup
directions: Cut vegetables in medium pieces.
Add onion soup mix and boil covered with water for 10 minutes.
Then lower heat and cook until vegetables are tender.

title: yeast bread
directions: Put yeast, water and sugar in bowl.
Stir and let stand in warm place; add to scalded milk, salt, sugar and butter.
Add flour, yeast and milk mixture.
Let rise 15 minutes, then knead down and let rise 15 minutes.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: "james" hot and spicy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; heat on stove at low temperature and simmer for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix butter, mustard, onion and poppy seeds.
Without separating rolls, remove from pans.
Split in half (easier if frozen).
Spread butter mixture on each side.
Place ham and cheese on bottom side.
Replace top side and return to pan.
Heat at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cut into roll size either before or after heating.
May be stored in freezer or refrigerator until ready to heat and serve.

title: carrot soup
directions: Cook carrots, potatoes and apple until soft in small amount of water, about 10 to 15 minutes. Pure in a blender.
Put 3 tablespoons of unsalted butter in soup pot.
Add curry powder to butter.
Add chicken broth and pureed carrot mixture.
Simmer soup for about 15 minutes, then add heavy cream.
Bring again to simmer.
Serve hot or cold with small croutons.

title: my fruit cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Add egg whites to butter-sugar mix.
Then add flour and vanilla.
Take 1/2 to 1 cup flour, to lightly flour nuts, fruit and raisins.
Fold in fruit and nut mixture into 1st mixture.
Pour in floured Bundt pan.
Place pan over pan of water while cooking.
Also place brown bag over top.
Cook 4 hours at 250°.
Use tester.

title: jiffy chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook mushrooms and onion in margarine until golden.
Blend in gravy, milk, 2 tablespoons grated cheese, poultry seasoning and sherry.
Place spaghetti in casserole.
Blend in half of gravy mixture.
Add chicken to remaining gravy mixture and pour over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Shred zucchini with peeling.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° or 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lazy pierogi casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with noodles to cover pan. Cook and mash potatoes and add to cottage cheese, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Use half of the mixture on one layer of noodles and remaining half on the second layer. End with noodles on top. Saute onions in butter and pour over top layer of noodles.
Sprinkle paprika on top. Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: family goulash
directions: Cook noodles in 1 1/2 quarts boiling water until tender, 7 to 10 minutes.
While noodles cook, cook and stir beef and onion in large skillet until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in drained noodles, celery, catsup, mushrooms with liquid, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all 7 ingredients together in a bowl. Remove crust from bread, cut into squares. Put the bread into a long baking pan. Add raisins and pecans on top of bread. Next, pour the custard mix on top. Cover with foil, pierce foil with a fork, in several places. Cook for 30 minutes at 350 degrees. Remove foil and brown for 10 minutes. Serve with butterscotch sauce over it.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco.
Add soda to water and gradually add all remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased pan.
Bake at 350° until edges brown slightly.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir once before pudding sets.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix ingredients with enough water to make 5 gallons.
Chill and serve.
Makes 5 gallons.

title: catalina veggie dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat in dressing.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Heat thoroughly and add 1 tablespoon sauteed onion (done in butter).

title: o' henry bars
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add Karo, vanilla and salt. Stir in oats (mixture will be sticky).
Press onto greased cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips together for 2 minutes in microwave or low heat on stove.
Stir well and spread on cooled crust.
Cool to set chocolate.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening. Add sugar gradually. Whip until sugar dissolves. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Pour in well-greased 10-inch tube pan and bake 1 hour and 5 minutes to 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy zucchini lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Reserve 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Mix remaining Mozzarella cheese, zucchini, Ricotta cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Spread 3/4 cup spaghetti sauce in ungreased rectangular baking dish (12 x 7-inch).
Top with 3 noodles.
Spread half of cheese mixture over noodles in dish.
Top with 3/4 cup of sauce. Repeat with 3 noodles, remaining cheese mixture and 3/4 cup sauce. Top with remaining noodles and sauce.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour or until noodles are tender.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle reserved Mozzarella cheese on top.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: peanut butter celery stuffer
directions: Cut celery into small chunks.
Stuff with peanut butter.

title: "depression" meat cakes or meat balls
directions: Put meat, eggs and onion in bowl; wet bread and add to bowl. Sprinkle salt and pepper over mixture and mix with hands until meat and bread are well blended.
If too wet, add more bread.
Shape into cakes and fry like hamburgers.
Use pan drippings to make gravy and serve with mashed potatoes.
Same recipe can be used for meat balls (add to mixture 1/2 cup parmesan cheese, 1 tablespoon granulated garlic and 1 teaspoon oregano); follow directions and shape meat in round balls.
Lay out on cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven about 1 hour or until done.
Drop into spaghetti sauce and simmer about 1/2 hour.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and shape into meatballs.
Blend last 5 ingredients for sauce to cover meatballs.
Place in a baking dish.
Cover and bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: party pizzas(snack)
directions: Brown beef and sausage together and drain.
Add cheese and remaining ingredients.
Spread on small party rye bread.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: taco dip
directions: Fry hamburger (drain if excessively greasy).
Combine remaining ingredients and cook in crock-pot until cheese is melted.
Keep warm while serving.
Serve with chips.

title: orange sauce (heart healthy)
directions: In pan, mix sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Gradually add boiling watter.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and cook, while stirring, for 5 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add oil, orange juice and rind and lemon juice.
Stir to mix well.
One tablespoon equals 35 calories.
Place sauce on plain cake, lemon cake, chocolate cake, pound cake, angel food cake or gingerbread.

title: cooked cabbage
directions: Put cabbage in pan.
Cover with water.
Add salt, pepper and shortening.
Cook on medium heat until tender.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix first four ingredients with apples; add water and butter.
Cook on top of stove until apples have a glaze.
Pour in casserole.
Drop flour mixture into apples; place in oven.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain; add taco seasoning mix (save 1 tablespoon).

title: crusty scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put into greased 2 quart casserole dish. Cut 2 slices of buttered bread to cubes. Sprinkle over tomato mixture. Bake 25 minutes at 375 degrees. Serve.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make cake according to directions on box (cool).

title: green chile fried chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine sour cream, milk, chile peppers, cilantro, lime juice, garlic, cumin, salt and black pepper. Place chicken pieces in a bag and set in a shallow dish. Pour sour cream mixture over chicken; seal bag. Refrigerate overnight; turn bag occasionally.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In medium skillet, heat Italian dressing and cook green pepper and onion over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until tender. Stir in tomatoes and simmer, covered, 15 minutes. Add shrimp and red pepper and simmer, covered, an additional 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink. To serve, arrange shrimp mixture over hot rice. Makes about 4 servings.

title: festive seafood cocktail
directions: Chill shrimp thoroughly.
Combine remaining ingredients for sauce.
Mix well and chill.
Arrange shrimp on cocktailer.

title: hungarian filled cookies
directions: Rub butter and flour between hands into large bowl.
Make well in center of dough.
Add egg yolks and cream (slightly mixed).
Work into smooth dough.
Chill overnight.
Roll out on slightly floured board.
Cut into 2-inch squares and fill center of each square with preserves.
Fold and pinch opposite corners together.
Bake on greased sheet at 350° for 25 minutes.
When slightly cooled, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 55 cookies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla; beat until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in zucchini.
Sift flour with cinnamon, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add to zucchini mixture. Fold in walnuts.
Pour mixture into 2 oiled and floured loaf pans. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until a tester comes out clean.
Let cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Invert loaves on rack and cool completely.

title: dirt(kids love this)
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Add softened cream cheese.
Beat until smooth, add Cool Whip and blend well.
Layer in new flower pot, bowl, etc.; first crushed cookies, then filling, ending with cookies.
You can add on top fresh or silk flowers, gummy worms, etc.
Makes 8 to 10 single recipe.
May be doubled.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Mix all together. Put in 12 muffin cups.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: kimchee
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until cabbage is tender. Place in jars and wait one week.

title: corn cake
directions: Stir corn kernels from cob and puree.
Add enough milk to obtain a soft mixture, then add beaten eggs.
Fold in sifted flour with salt.
Add melted butter and sugar last.
Turn into greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes until golden or inserted cake tester comes out clean.
Let cool and cut into pieces.

title: stuffed cabbage(golumbki, polish specialty)
directions: Core cabbage and place in boiling water.
Parboil until leaves are pliable and start to separate.
Drain.
Remove cabbage and separate leaves.
Trim thick veins off each cabbage leaf.
Saute onion until yellow.
Remove from heat.

title: pepper steak with noodles
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Cut beef into thin strips and brown in butter. Sprinkle with garlic and cook, stirring occasionally until brown.
Add onion and green peppers.
Cook 2 minutes or until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes and bouillon cube.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk until smooth.
Cook on medium heat 6 minutes while constantly stirring until thickened.
Add cheese and the next 3 ingredients, stirring until cheese melts.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown
beef.
Drain well.
Combine meat, seasonings and tomato paste.
Cut
bread
lengthwise
and
into serving size pieces. Spread
meat mixture on top of pieces and broil for 5 to 10 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle cheese on top and broil until melted.

title: peach salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Cool and add marshmallows, drained pineapple and sliced bananas. Refrigerate until set.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Use a big bowl.
Add all ingredients but flour and mix with a spoon until mixed.
Add 2 cups of flour and mix, then add the other 2 cups of flour.
Bake on a cookie sheet, about 12 to 13 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly to cover bottom of pan.
Combine thawed strawberries and Jell-O; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat 3 minutes.
Pour batter over marshmallows.
Spoon strawberry mixture evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped topping.

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Blend butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add mashed bananas and vanilla.
Stir.
Alternate adding flour (with baking soda and salt) and milk to batter.
Fill baking cups 2/3 full.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Pour milk over coconut and set aside while creaming the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, to this and beat well.
Add milk, coconut and flavoring.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake about 30 minutes in 350° oven or until golden brown and firm.
Do not overbake.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook, drain and squeeze the chopped spinach.
Add all the other ingredients.
Make into 3/4-inch balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat; add onions.
Cook until soft.
Add chili powder; let cook 5 minutes, then add all ingredients except vinegar. Simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Add vinegar about 10 minutes before removing from heat.
(I prefer to add beans about halfway through cooking.) Serves 6 to 8.
If used for
6 servings, contains 21 g fat and 308 calories per serving.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, marshmallow cream and lemon juice.
Serve with apples, grapes, strawberries, etc.
Be sure to refrigerate.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake until golden brown about 40 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares.

title: italian codfish
directions: Soak codfish overnight in cold water; changing water several times.
Saute onions, olives, celery and capers in olive oil. Stir occasionally.
Add crushed tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Add codfish.
Add enough water to cover fish. Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.

title: scalded tennessee corn cakes
directions: Add salt to water; bring to a boil.
Gradually mix meal with water.
Cool until firm.
Shape into patties.
Fry in 1-inch fat until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Drain and serve hot.
Makes 18 corn cakes.

title: hank's favorite potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until tender; while still warm, pare and dice.
Add onions, mayonnaise, celery seed, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix thoroughly and chill.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cashew refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually creaming thoroughly.
Add eggs, nuts and vanilla and beat well.
Add flour gradually, mixing thoroughly.
Shape into rolls and wrap in wax paper.
Chill overnight.

title: quick and easy salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 2 tablespoons of juice.
In medium mixing bowl, mix salmon, egg and onion until sticky.
Stir in flour.
Add baking powder to salmon juice.
Stir into salmon mixture.
Form into small patties and fry 5 minutes until brown in hot oil.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: candy apples
directions: Wash apples, remove stems and insert skewers into stem end. Mix together sugar, corn syrup and water in a heavy 2 quart saucepan. Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat until mixture boils and sugar dissolves, then cook without stirring until temperature reaches 250° on candy thermometer or until a small amount forms soft balls in cold water. Add cinnamon candies and continue cooking to 285°. Remove from heat; stir in red food coloring. Dip apples. Place on lightly greased baking sheet to cool.

title: jello-cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix Jell-O (dry) and cottage cheese. Add drained fruit and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: dirt cups
directions: You will also need 8 to 10 plastic cups.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches. Brown beef and onion. Drain. Stir in salt and pepper. Spread in plate. Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth. Use blender or hand mixer on high. Pour into plate. Bake 25 minutes. Top with tomatoes. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: parmesan breaded chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a shallow bowl. Dip chicken in buttermilk and roll in bread crumb mixture. Coat a baking pan with cooking spray. Place chicken (bone side down if not boneless) on pan. Bake, covered, in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes. Remove cover and bake another 20 minutes or until done. Makes 4 servings.

title: rhubarb creme
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You can also use apples or peaches.

title: sally's prize blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir flour, salt and baking powder in medium bowl.
Mix with sugar and slowly stir in milk to make batter.
Melt butter in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Dump blueberries into batter and sprinkle cinnamon and lemon peel on top of mixture.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Heat at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes and serve.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown the ground
beef, onions, garlic and green pepper in
a small amount of oil.
Add the tomatoes, tomato paste and 3 cans tomato sauce.
Stir in the salt, pepper, Accent, herbs, steak and Tabasco
sauces and simmer for 4 hours, until thick. Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.

title: burgundy pecan burgers
directions: Lightly mix ground beef, pecans, salt and pepper.
Shape into 4 patties.
Brown on both sides.
Drain.
Add wine and onion. Cover; simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove patties to platter.
Blend water and cornstarch.
Add to pan juices.
Cook and stir until boiling.
Pour over patties on serving platter.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate heath bar dessert
directions: Crush cookies and add melted margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding, ice cream and milk together.
Pour this mixture into crust and chill.
Cover with 9 ounces Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with 2 crushed Heath bars.

title: nut and cheese log
directions: Put pecans and garlic through medium blade of food chopper. Blend next 6 ingredients in bowl; mix in ground nuts.
Shape in a roll 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Sprinkle chili powder.
Wrap tightly in wax paper.
Chill log at least 4 hours.
Slice before serving or leave as log.
Allow to soften at room temperature. Serve with crackers.
Yields 1 log.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken. Dip in Crisco oil and roll in corn flake crumbs.
Salt
to
taste.
Place
in
large
pan or dish. Bake 15 minutes at
450° or 45 minutes at 350°.
Do not turn at all.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together.
Store in jars.
For flavored hot chocolate mix: Measure out 4 to 6 cups of regular hot chocolate mix and add 1 small jar of flavored coffee creamer (Irish cream, French vanilla or any other flavored creamer).
This mix can be stored in small jars and make nice gifts.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and add enough mayonnaise to make the consistency you prefer.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Place margarine in a baking dish and place in a preheated 375° oven.
Watch carefully while melting margarine.

title: marinated veggie salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Cool.
Combine vegetables and stir in vinegar mixture.
Cover and place in refrigerator 12 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: cheese and crabmeat hors d'oeuvre
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except muffins) and spoon on muffins.
Cut each muffin into four pieces and broil until bubbly.

title: amie's corn relish
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a heavy pot.
Simmer until thick, stirring as needed.
About halfway done, add the rest of the ingredients.
Taste and add more until "right".
Seal in hot pint jars or freeze.
Serve as you would any relish.

title: party crackers
directions: Mix together well.
Let set 3 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion in salted water and drain. Combine chicken soup and sour cream. Fold in drained squash and onion. Combine stuffing mix and margarine.

Spread half of the stuffing mix in bottom of one large casserole dish or two small ones. Spoon vegetables mix atop. Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over vegetables. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 large servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
While macaroni is cooking, make cheese sauce.
In large saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in flour and mustard and cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk, then Worcestershire sauce.
Continue to cook, stirring, until thickened and boiling.
Remove from heat and stir in 2 cups of the Cheddar and Parmesan cheese until blended.
Drain macaroni well.
Stir into cheese sauce until well blended.
Turn into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: fried bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening; add water.
Make soft dough.
Pat out small portion and fry in shortening.
Drain on towel.
Add powdered sugar and honey, beans and cheese, shredded beef and salsa or your choice.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Do not use metal bowls or spoons for any portion of recipe.

title: natural apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine apples, water and lemon juice in large bowl.
Combine brown sugar, flour and cinnamon; toss with apples.
Layer in an 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Combine cereal and margarine; sprinkle evenly over apple mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until apples are tender.
Serve warm. Top with frozen yogurt, whipped cream or ice cream.

title: grandmother's buttermilk biscuits
directions: Work shortening into buttermilk.
Add soda, salt and baking powder.
From a sifter, stir flour into mixture to the proper consistency.
Choose now to either flour the dough and cut out biscuits or add dough directly to a greased pan from a tablespoon for drop biscuits (in which case less flour is used for a thinner consistency).
In either case, bake at 425°.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute the onions and celery in the butter.
Add the flour to thicken saute.
Add the clam juice and cook slowly until thickened. Add the bouillon cubes, clams and potatoes.
Throw in some salt pork.
Cook all together until flavors are all blended. Remove the salt pork and then add the half and half cream.
Heat just a few more minutes and serve.

title: baked tulips
directions: Grease 6 muffin tins.
Remove crust from bread and butter 1 side.
Push buttered side down into muffin pan.
The corners will stick up.
Break 1 egg into each bread-lined cup; salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until egg is done as you like it.

title: wil's crab cakes
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except crab).
Add crab. (If too dry, add more mayonnaise.)
Fry about 5 minutes on each side (medium temperature).

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the pie shell, in a bowl; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Prepare berries and crush enough to make 1 cup; leave the rest whole.
Combine crushed berries, sugar, water and cornstarch. Bring to boil.
Cook over low heat 2 to 3 minutes or until clear, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Add butter and a few drops of food coloring.
Cool slightly.
Combine whole berries with cooled mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: creamy dill dip(low-fat recipe)
directions: Combine ingredients; cover and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: super stuffed pizza loaf
directions: In small bowl, combine picante sauce and tomato paste; mix well.
In large bowl, combine meat, sausage (casing removed), 1/2 cup sauce mixture, onion, crumbs, egg and seasoning.
Mix well. Divide in half.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in a casserole dish. Top with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add the preceeding ingredients as listed.
Mix well and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: broccoli and corn dish
directions: Melt butter and stir in bread crumbs.
Mix corn, broccoli, egg and all but 2 tablespoons of the bread crumbs.
Put in dish with the 2 tablespoons bread crumbs sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350° uncovered 60 to 70 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo, shortening, sugar, and vanilla. Add egg; mix until fluffy. Stir in flour, soda, and salt. Stir until mixture is smooth; blend in milk.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Slowly blend all ingredients. Chill.

title: caramel coconut bars
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add flour and baking powder.
Heat milk and butter until butter melts.
Add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Crush box of Cheez-Its crackers.
Mix in garlic and onion powder.
Add melted butter to moisten.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon pears
directions: Peel pears and slice in half rounds or spears.
Soak overnight in 1 gallon water and lime.
Next morning, drain, rinse and soak in clear water for 4 hours.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion, margarine and celery salt until tender.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
Mix all ingredients together; simmer for 30 minutes.
You can add all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on slow for 4 hours.

title: stromboli
directions: Take bread dough and let rise.
Roll out to about 8 x 10-inch. Mix Worcestershire sauce and mustard; then brush on dough.
Put chipped ham, Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Sprinkle with oregano and garlic salt.
Fold over and seal with water.
Place seam side down on greased cookie sheet.
Brush top with melted butter.
Put slits on top (don't go all the way through). Sprinkle with garlic and oregano.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes. Turn oven to 350° and finish baking for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: frozen strawberry preserves
directions: Place the strawberries and 2 cups sugar in a large pan; bring to a boil.
Boil for 4 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Add 2 more cups sugar and bring to a boil; boil 5 minutes.
Let cool and skim foam off with metal spoon.
Place in a container and freeze.

title: easy chicken parmigian
directions: Dip each chicken breast in milk or water to moisten it, and then dip it in the bread crumbs.
Place in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Add the spaghetti sauce and sprinkle oregano and a little grated Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake for 10 more minutes.
Top with the shredded Mozzarella cheese and bake for 5 minutes or until the cheese melts.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Add ground beef to spaghetti sauce.
Put 1/3 in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Layer with noodles.
Mix eggs and cottage cheese; add 1/2 mixture and 1/2 pound Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat.
Put sauce mixture on the top.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti by directions; drain and cool.
Cut onion, pepper and tomato in small pieces.
Add to cooled spaghetti.
Add Zesty Italian dressing and 2/3 bottle of Salad Supreme.
Mix well and refrigerate.
You may leave out the onion and add a salad topping if desired.

title: ham that am so good!
directions: Use either butt or shank or whole smoked ham depending on how many kids are coming home.
Soak ham in water, changing several times for 4 to 5 hours.
This is to remove a lot of salt from the ham.
Boil ham in apple juice for 4 to 5 hours.
Let ham cool in apple juice.
Trim excess fat.
Cover with brown sugar, decorate with pineapple slices, maraschino cherries and whole brown cloves. Bake in 300° oven until glaze is formed.

title: rice pudding 1
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients on stove over a low flame about 1 hour.
Stir once in awhile.
Remove from burner. Beat together egg yolks, 1/4 cup sugar, vanilla and raisins.
Add this to stove mixture.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: mango pie
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in hot water and cool it. Add cream cheese, sour cream and sugar. Blend well. Pour in a baked pie crust and refrigerate overnight.

title: taco meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° until done.

title: hearty baked macaroni
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray a 9 x 9 x 2-inch casserole with vegetable oil spray.
In a small bowl, combine tomato puree, water, Italian seasoning and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder.
In another bowl, combine cottage cheese, onion powder and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder.

title: ruby's brownies
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
In bowl, beat eggs with a fork. Add sugar.
Pour melted oleo into bowl and stir.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: In saucepan, put chicken, vegetables with seasonings, water and ginger; cook on medium high until bubbly.
Cover saucepan; turn burner to low.
Cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
In a bowl, put orange juice and cornstarch.
Mix into chicken mixture; cook 2 minutes more.
Spoon chicken mixture over the noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple chicken sauté
directions: Cut chicken in small bites; heat in 2 tablespoons oil.
Saute until cooked.
Stir constantly, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from pan. Saute bell pepper and apple until tender.
Add other tablespoon oil, if necessary.
Add chicken back to apples and pepper. Combine other ingredients and add to the mixture.
Cook until thickened.

title: green pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding and Cool Whip thoroughly. Add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix. Refrigerate.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with cooked chicken or turkey pieces, about a 1-inch layer.
Mix together cream of celery soup, dry onion soup mix and sour cream.
Cover chicken layer with this mixture.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mildred's salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well and let stand for 30 minutes before serving.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Put 2/3 on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Slice and smooth ice cream on top of mix. (Ice cream should be softened.) Add remaining 1/3 of mix on top.
Freeze.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water and oatmeal.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time, beat.
Sift flour, measure, resift with soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add oatmeal last. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dilly cucumber salad
directions: Place cucumbers in a large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients except dill weed; pour over cucumbers and gently mix.
Sprinkle with dill weed.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Mix lightly before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: heavenly chocolate cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon in bowl and set aside.
Put in pan to boil: margarine, cocoa, oil and water. Bring to a boil.
Then pour dry ingredients into this and mix at medium speed.
Then add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured sheet pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: pickled mushrooms and onions
directions: In small saucepan, combine all ingredients, except mushrooms. Bring to a boil.
Add mushrooms; simmer 5 to 6 minutes.
Pour into bowl and cover.
Chill several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Drain and serve with cocktail picks.

title: easy shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt butter and add flour.
Stir until the roux is medium brown.
Add vegetables and cook until they are tender.
Add water, shrimp and seasonings.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: pan bread
directions: Mix together water and yeast.
Add all other ingredients.
Turn out onto floured board.
Knead 5 minutes.
Heat oven slightly then turn off.
Put dough into greased bowl and place in warmed oven. Let rise for 45 minutes (until double the size).
Spread in pizza pan.
Put back into warm oven to rise again (30 minutes).
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Take out of oven and butter top.
Cut in pizza wedges.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together with fork.
Place in greased small loaf pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mother's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream sugar and Parkay.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat well after adding each egg.
Sift flour into mixture, alternating with milk.
Add salt, vanilla and butter flavors.
Spray a tube pan with Baker's Joy.
Pour into pan; bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion, garlic powder, pepper and Ragu sauce. Simmer until onions are tender.

title: elegant stuffed chicken
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, over medium heat, melt butter.
Add zucchini and cook until tender, about 2 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove from heat.
Into pan, tear bread into small pieces. Stir in egg, cheese, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Carefully loosen skin on each chicken quarter by pushing fingers between skin and meat to form pocket.
Spoon some stuffing into each pocket.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until fork-tender.

title: wy's waffles
directions: Beat eggs and add buttermilk; stir in remaining ingredients. Beat with a rotary beater until smooth.
Cook in hot waffle iron. Makes about 3 medium to large waffles.

title: squash bread
directions: Mix together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spiced cranberry punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Boil 5 minutes.
Strain and mix with fruit juices.
Just before serving, pour over a decorative ice ring mold (use holly leaves and red cranberries).
Add ginger ale.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix ingredients until blended.
Refrigerate about 2 hours. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: crystal light lemon pie
directions: Prepare the pudding with the milk per directions.
Add the Crystal Light; mix until thick.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: breast of turkey on broccoli morney
directions: Cook broccoli spears in lightly salted boiling water for 5 to 8 minutes or just until done.
In small saucepan, melt butter and add flour; mix well. Add scalded milk, salt and pepper and simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Add Cheddar and stir until melted.

title: skillet gumbo
directions: Combine all ingredients, except rice, in heavy large skillet. Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in rice. Replace lid and simmer for 20 minutes or until rice is tender. Stir in file just before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon bars
directions: First, make bottom layer.
Blend the butter and sugar until creamy.
Stir in flour until crumbly, pat into bottom of a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 18 minutes.
While this bakes, beat the eggs with the sugar, lemon and flour.
Pour this over the still warm crust, and return to the oven 18 minutes. Cool in pan before cutting into squares.
Then watch them disappear.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown chuck roast.
Mix all remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Bring to a boil on top of the stove.
Pour over meat. Bake for 6 hours at 275°.
Remove from oven.
Take fork and remove fat and flake off meat.
Serves a crew.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Chop onion;
simmer in butter for 5 minutes.
Add broccoli; cook another 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Add cheese last. Cook until rice is soft and cheese is melted, about 30 minutes in 350° oven, uncovered.

title: hamburger puffs
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add onions and saute until golden brown.
Crumble bread into mixing bowl; add milk.
Let stand until bread is moist.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add onion, green pepper and salt.
Add meat and mix well.
Pile mixture lightly into greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pans.
Top each with thin onion slice. Bake in 425° oven until browned, about 30 minutes.

title: soup burgers
directions: Brown hamburg and onion together; drain off grease.
Add mustard and ketchup.
Stir together.
Add 1 can vegetable soup. Stir and add a little water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Put on toasted buns.

title: banana fritters
directions: First make batter.
Sift flour and salt; stir in beaten egg and melted butter.
Add milk and mix well.
Beat egg white until stiff, then fold into batter.

title: marsha's corn casserole
directions: Mix butter and corn in casserole dish.
Mix the sour cream and egg together.
Add to corn.
Add dry Jiffy mix; stir until smooth. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken #1
directions: In greased casserole, put layer of chicken, tortillas, cheese and onions.
Repeat layers.
Mix soup, Ro-Tel and broth.
Pour over all and heat in 375° oven until bubbly and hot through (about 40 minutes).
This freezes well so can be made ahead!

title: vanilla granola
directions: Combine all ingredients except cherries.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 25 minutes or until golden.
Stir at least twice while baking.
Stir in cherries when cooled.
Store in airtight container for up to 1 month.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain fat and add onions, pepper, chili powder and rice.
Cook until onions change color.
Pour into 4-quart casserole dish and pour tomatoes over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brandy slush
directions: Mix all ingredients in large container.
Freeze, stirring occasionally.
Fill glass 2/3 full with slush, remainder with 7-Up.
Garnish with fruit on a toothpick and serve with a straw.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle top with a cup of crushed potato chips.
Bake 1 hour in greased pan at 350°.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix carrots, soup and cheese together and put in casserole. Mix margarine (melted) with cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. (Make cooked carrots for a short time prior to mixing as directed.)

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, peanut butter, vanilla, and dry ingredients.
Pour batter into greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°F for 25 min.
Put 1 1/2 c. chocolate chips on top to melt as soon as taken out of oven.
In advance, mix 1 c. icing sugar, 1/3 c. peanut butter, add 3-5 Tbsp. milk.
Pour this on top of melted chocolate chips and swirl slightly.
If you swirl it too much, it will look like chocolate frosting.
Cut into bars while slightly warm.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans thoroughly; place in large pot.
Cover with water. Add 2 tablespoons salt and soak overnight.
In the morning, drain well and add 2 quarts of water and ham hocks.
Bring to boil and simmer slowly 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add large chopped onion, crushed tomato, juice of lemon, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer another 1/2 hour or longer if desired.
Freezes well.
May be made ahead of time.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip in a large bowl and put in the refrigerator overnight or for half a day.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: wedding punch
directions: Boil 3 cups water and sugar until dissolved. Add Jell-O and 1 gallon of water. Stir in juices and flavoring. Chill and add ginger ale just before serving. Serves 50.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt well. Add liquid ingredients. Bake in oblong cake pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: holiday peanut butter cups
directions: In a large bowl, combine first five ingredients; mix well. Form peanut butter mixture into 1-inch balls.
Press balls into miniature 1-inch baking cups with your thumb.
Top each with a 1/2 tablespoon melted chocolate.
Chill one hour.
Store in container with tight fitting lid.
Tastes like Reese's Peanut Butter Cups.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place rolls in 10 x 15 pan and press seams together.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° and cool completely.
Mix cream cheese and dressing and pour on top of crust.
Top with vegetables and cheese.
Press down slightly.
Chill.

title: baked apples with currants(elegant with roast pork)
directions: Slice a piece from the bottom of each apple, so it will sit firmly in the baking dish.
Core each apple, being careful not to pierce through the bottom.
Make a well in center of each apple (where you've removed core) large enough to hold a generous amount of the filling.
Mix filling ingredients together, except cinnamon. Place apples in a buttered baking dish.
Stuff each apple with filling.
Place a cinnamon stick in center of each.
Bake apples in a 300° oven for 30 to 35 minutes, until they are soft, yet still retain their shape.
Yields 12 servings.

title: dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake in loaf pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Crumble.
Top with ice cream.

title: meat loaf surprise
directions: Needed:
Loaf pan or oblong pan or casserole.

title: great beginnings pasquet egg
directions: Place eggs in an egg carton and cut the tops off with an egg cutter.
Empty eggs into bowl and rinse the shell with cold water, pulling the loose shell and membrane away from the top.
Drain shell.

title: crab delight dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve on crackers or crisp raw vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pear cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add dry ingredients, sifted.
Fold in pears and nuts. Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: peach and maraschino cherry jam
directions: Chop up fine or put through food grinder.
Put in pan and bring to boil.
After it starts to boil, continue boiling and stirring for 20 minutes.
Then remove from stove and put into jam jars and seal.

title: two hour rolls
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt. Add water and mix well in mixer.
Add butter and mix. Add eggs and the remaining flour.
Knead, cover and let set 30 minutes.
Punch down and shape into rolls for greased pan.
Let rise until double. Bake at 425° for 10 or 15 minutes.
Mixture may be refrigerated overnight.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water, then stir into other ingredients.

title: broiled parmesan potatoes
directions: Stir together margarine or butter, basil, paprika, garlic powder and black pepper.
Brush margarine mixture on both sides of potato slices and place in a single layer on a cookie sheet or broiler pan.
Broil about 5 inches from the heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until potatoes begin to brown.
Turn potatoes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Broil 6 to 8 minutes more or until tender.

title: sausage hash brown casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage; set aside.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Put half into a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle with the sausage.
Cover with remaining potato mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until golden.

title: slow cooking round steak with rich gravy
directions: Cut steak into 5 to 6 serving-size pieces.
Place in slow cooking pot.
Add dry soup mix, water and soup.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Excellent when served with mashed potatoes. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: jam cake
directions: In a bowl, cream butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat eggs one at a time.
Stir in grape jam and milk.
Beat flour and spices.
Beat until smooth and fluffy; fold in pecans.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake in a preheated slow oven (325°) for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Unmold and cool on a rack.

title: candy apple walnut pie(made easy with pet ritz crust)
directions: In large bowl, toss together apples, walnuts, cinnamon candies, 1/3 cup sugar and flour.
Pour into one frozen pie crust.
Break or crumble second frozen crust into small pieces; toss with remaining 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in preheated 375° oven on preheated baking sheet for 55 to 60 minutes or until candies melt and bubble up through the crumbled crust.
Cool completely before serving.
Makes 8 servings.
Mm good.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and mix in 1/2 of the tomato sauce mixture.
Shape into oval loaf and place in baking dish.
Pour remainder of tomato sauce on top of meat.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: my men's cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Blend in cereal, coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until browned, about 8 to 12 minutes.
Flatten cookies slightly with fork before removing from pan.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen, depending on size of cookies.

title: corn relish
directions: Drop ears of corn into boiling water.
Boil for 5 minutes. Dip into cold water; cut from cob.
Measure and combine with remaining ingredients and boil for 15 minutes. Pack into sterilized jars, to within 1/2-inch of top.
Put on caps; tighten bands.
Process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes or 5 pounds pressure, just until kettle comes to pressure.
Makes 5 to 6 pints.
Twenty-two ears of corn will do 7 pints.

title: quick sweet dill pickles
directions: Slice enough thin, unpeeled cucumbers to make 4 quarts.
Allow to stand overnight, sprinkling with 6 tablespoons of salt and adding water to make brine.
Drain well.
Cover with weak vinegar,* adding 1 cup of sugar and 1 teaspoon of celery seed to each quart of pickles.
Bring to a boil and seal.
Makes approximately 4 quarts.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Mix sugar, mustard and cornstarch; slowly stir in vinegar. Add rest of ingredients; stir over low heat until thickened. Makes about 2 cups.

title: cake balls
directions: Empty brown sugar into beaten eggs; beat.
Toss in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake 30 minutes in a greased 9x9 inch pan at 350°.
Cool.
With teaspoon, shape into balls; then dip balls into sifted granulated sugar.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of peppers (remove inner fillers).
Parboil peppers 2 to 3 minutes before stuffing.
Mix ham, corn, tomatoes and 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Fill peppers.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix and cook in 4-quart pan until mixture strings from spoon into pan.
Add peanuts and cook about 20 minutes or until honey-colored.
Add butter.
Melt.
Add soda and mix through.
Pour into pan, spreading to peanut brittle thickness.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender, drain.
Mix next four ingredients with potatoes and pour into a greased casserole dish, cover.
Bake in oven until bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Crush crackers.
Pour over casserole.
Pour melted butter over crackers. Put back in oven a few minutes, then serve warm.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat.
Stir in brown sugar until blended; let cool. Stir in egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together in bowl. Add to mixture.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Spread in well-greased 9-inch square glass baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes or until tests done.

title: french market soup
directions: *Black beans, red beans, navy beans, garbanzos, pinto beans, baby lima beans, lentils, barley, split peas and black-eyed peas.

title: wrapped chicken
directions: Line bottom of dish with beef.
Wrap bacon around chicken. Pour cream of chicken, sour cream and mushrooms over chicken. Cook, uncovered, at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: layered salad(yes, it can taste like mine!)
directions: In a large container, (I use the top of a sheet cake cover), layer first 5 ingredients as they are listed. Then, about 30 minutes or so before you serve, layer the rest of the ingredients.

title: snappy bean bake
directions: Drain beans; put half of them in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Blend soup, milk, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and ripe olives. Turn half of it over beans; sprinkle with half the potato chips. Repeat with beans, soup and chips.
Bake in moderately hot oven (375°) for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: beef sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into 3-inch patties, 1/4-inch thick.
Fry these as you would a hamburg patty.

title: microwave chestnut bites
directions: Drain chestnuts.
Cut bacon strips in half.
Wrap around chestnut and use toothpick to hold in place.
Dip in barbecue sauce.
Arrange on plate and place in microwave for about 4 minutes.

title: white icing
directions: Beat together first 4 ingredients.
Add 1/4 cup boiling water. Beat until peaks stand up.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes, then add potatoes.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: pecan praline cake
directions: The temperature of the buttermilk is what makes the cake, about 110°.
Warm buttermilk and butter.
Put in mixing bowl.
Add brown sugar and eggs.
Beat.
Add dry ingredients, sifted together.
Beat well. Add vanilla. Bake in greased and floured rectangular 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: kugel
directions: Blend 6 to 8 eggs with beater.
Add sugar and salt.
Blend all together with blender.
Spread butter in pan for sticking purposes.
Cook noodles.
Spread noodles in pan.
Pour egg mixture on noodles.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add raisins, if you like. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered; uncover last 10 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix salt, sugar, flour, milk and vanilla. Pour over butter; do not stir.
Put peaches on top of batter; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: pecan cracker snack bites
directions: Cook Eagle Brand milk, dates and pecans, stirring until thick. Remove from heat; add cream cheese and enough powdered sugar to make the consistency of icing; spread on crackers.

title: sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice until tender but not mushy.
Drain.
Cook sausage until crumbly.
Pour off fat.
Stir in drained mushrooms and soup. Add rice.
Put layer of rice mixture in buttered casserole.
Top with thinly sliced onion.
Put remainder of rice mixture over the top.
Cover casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes. Serves 4.

title: man-approved quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9 or 10-inch pie pan. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion evenly over bottom of pie pan. Place remaining ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed for 1 minute.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage well and drain.
Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan. Place bread over oleo in pan.
Sprinkle drained sausage over bread. Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over mixture.
Chill for 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: salad
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower in bite size pieces.
Toss together with bacon, cheese and raisins.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; pour over salad.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into graham cracker pie crust.

title: apple butter(oven)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in oven at 350° for 3 hours. Stir 3 times during this time.
Twenty minutes before done, add 2 tablespoons cinnamon and 1 tablespoon cloves.
Return to oven for 20 minutes.
Apple butter can be sealed in jars for storage.

title: double lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil, water and cake mix together.
Mix until smooth. Bake in a greased cake pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken pepper gnocchi
directions: Coat a large, nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add red peppers and the next 5 ingredients; saute until tender.
Stir in salt, flour and bouillon granules.
Gradually add water; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Set aside and keep warm.
Cook pasta according to directions, omitting salt and fat.
Drain and set aside.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nonalcoholic milk shake with vanilla ice cream(dose for 500 grs.)
directions: Blend the milk and the egg until it becomes one soft mixture. Add the crushed ice, then put in the vanilla ice cream.
Blend for a little while and serve.

title: chocolate dip candy
directions: Mix all ingredients and make into small balls.
Place in refrigerator for several hours.
With toothpick, dip in melted chocolate and place on wax paper to harden.

title: "not" champagne punch
directions: Combine, serve at once over ice.

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: Combine milk, pudding mix, pumpkin spice and whipped topping in a deep narrowed-bottom bowl.
Beat at lowest speed of electric mixer for 1 minute.
Pour into pie shells.

title: olive loaf
directions: Make ahead and refrigerate (a few hours is best).

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in refrigerator.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix together cornbread, crumbs and stock until well blended. Beat eggs slightly; add milk, salt and pepper.
Add to bread mixture.
Add chopped celery, poultry seasoning and chopped onion. Stir well.
Bake in well-greased pan at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes. Makes 8 cups.

title: country grits and sausage
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil.
Stir in grits.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat; cook 4 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Combine grits and cheese in a large bowl.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: appetizer cheese mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Place over boiling water, stirring until dissolved.
Mix into sour cream.
Add dressing mix, Blue cheese and cottage cheese; beat until well blended.
Pour into 3 1/2-cup ring mold or small loaf pan; chill until firm.
Unmold. Garnish with parsley and carrot curls.
Serve with crackers.

title: apple pie
directions: Sprinkle flour on one ready made pie crust.
Place, floured side down, over a 9-inch pie pan.
Trim bottom crust even with pan edge.
Combine ingredients in a large bowl and fill in pie crust. Add the second crust to the top; cut slits in top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool completely on a wire rack.

title: butterscotch torte
directions: Mix margarine and flour.
Use fingers to work margarine through flour.
Add 1/2 cup nuts.
Press this mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain; salt very little. Mix all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart dish. Save at least 1/2 can of onion rings and put on top last 5 minutes of baking. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sugarless peach-apple butter
directions: In a 4-quart kettle mash peaches well; add apple juice.
Bring to boiling point, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and boil gently, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes or until very thick.
Stir often as mixture thickens.
Press mixture through a sieve or food mill.
Ladle into hot clean jars (1/2 pint).
A good spread for toast or biscuits.

title: pizza sticks
directions: Separate and unroll breadsticks.
Place 3 pepperoni slices over half of each breadstick.
Fold breadstick in half; seal end and twist.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with mixture of Parmesan cheese, Italian seasoning and garlic.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fudge muffins
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine together.	Stir in sugar and vanilla. Add flour and just mix. Fill cupcake liners 2/3 full. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. You can add chocolate chips also, and they are doubly chocolate.

title: vegetable sandwich
directions: Soften cream cheese.
In mixing bowl add other ingredients. Beat until well mixed.
Spread on bread of your choice.

title: cinnamon hearts
directions: Mix cinnamon and applesauce together.
Knead and roll until you have a dough-like mixture.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at low temperature (200°) for 3 hours or air dry 6 days on a screen.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and spread evenly into a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally while baking.
This will
make a crumbly mixture. Reserve 2/3 cup for topping.

title: posh squash
directions: Cook squash in boiling salted water until tender; drain and cool.
Combine mayonnaise, cheese, onion, eggs, salt and pepper. Stir well.
Add squash, stirring gently.
Pour into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and butter. Spoon over squash mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then stir in zucchini and vanilla. Add remaining ingredients and stir well. Bake in greased loaf pan for 45 to 60 minutes until tests done.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Mix all together and put in large casserole dish.
Sprinkle the corn flakes on top and cut oleo on top.

title: banana-strawberry dessert
directions: Mix vanilla pudding according to directions and fold in Cool Whip.
Layer ingredients in a glass dish, starting with cake and ending with pudding mixture.
Repeat.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss first four ingredients with Miracle Whip/mayonnaise sugar and vinegar.

title: cranberry pineapple chutney
directions: Drain pineapple and put aside.
Mix its juice with sugar, cranberries, raisins, spices, salt and cayenne in a heavy saucepan.
Cook to boiling.
Lower heat and simmer 20 minutes. Add pineapple; simmer 10 minutes more.
Keep either in deep freeze or refrigerate if paraffin sealed.

title: taco salad tostada
directions: Cook and season ground beef with taco seasoning as directed on package. Spread each crisped tortilla with 1 tablespoon of the nacho cheese sauce. Top with meat mixture and lettuce. Crumble 1 taco shell over each tostada. Top evenly with tomato, shredded cheese and salsa. Makes 6 servings, 1 tostada each.

title: turkey strata
directions: Layer all ingredients in an 8 x 8-inch dish.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Mix half package of meat with other ingredients; form a ball. Cover ball with remaining beef.
Refrigerate several hours.
Cover with plastic wrap.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil lightly.
Add cabbage and celery and cook for 5 minutes.
Add other vegetables, tomato sauce and water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add herbs.
If you want it more soupy, you can add more water or sauce.
Can also add other vegetables like potatoes or broccoli.
If you want, you can cook some small pasta (ditalini or small shells) and add to soup.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover bottom of pan with coconut and pecan pieces.
Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour over coconut and pecans.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add all other ingredients and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Can be cooked as muffins.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325° to 350°.
By hand, cream softened butter, brown sugar and white sugar until just blended. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together. Combine dry ingredients and mix with butter mixture. Stir in the chocolate chips.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 4 pieces.
Roll in cinnamon, sugar and brown sugar.
Put half of coated biscuits in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Pour over 1/2 stick butter and pecan chips and 1/2 of sugar mixture.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, then pour over glaze (powdered sugar, milk, vanilla and melted butter).
Pull apart and enjoy.

title: cowboy coffee cafe
directions: Arrange biscuits in a lightly greased 9-in. round cake pan, overlapping edges.
Combine remaining ingredients, spread evenly over biscuits.
Bake at 350 degrees for 22 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli as directed.
Prepare rice as directed.
Mix all together and put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: herb marinated chicken
directions: Cook your favorite way.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Add shortening to flour and blend with pastry blender or use 2 knives, cutting shortening into flour until particles are about the size of peas.
Add salt, vinegar and milk.
Mix well and chill one day (can be left in fridge longer).
Allow dough to reach room temperature before using.

title: red cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Mix cocoa and food coloring to make a paste.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk and flour and salt alternately.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Dissolve the soda in the vinegar.
Bake in 3 layer pans at 350° about 30 minutes or until done.

title: christmas carol cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray 12-cup Bundt pan with Baker's Joy.
Combine ingredients in order listed; blend well after each. Pour into pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool for 45 minutes.
Invert on platter.
Glaze and decorate.

title: red rice 1
directions: Fry bacon until crispy.
Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Add tomato sauce and season to taste.
Add cooked rice and then add crumbled up bacon.
Let rice simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning mix together. Spread on bottom of dish.
Top with lettuce, cheese, tomatoes and olives.

title: simple peanut butter candy
directions: Mix together peanut butter and Marshmallow Fluff.
Let stand while you boil white sugar and water until it spins a thread (a good 3 minutes).
Add sugar/water mixture to the peanut butter/Fluff mixture.
Beat well until it starts to thicken. Pour into 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.
Cut when cool or warm.

title: german chocolate's cousin cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, sour cream, eggs,
oil and water together. Add chocolate chips, chocolate bar (grated) and pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube or Bundt pan.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Spray Pam on Dutch oven.
Place meat on bottom.
Layer onion, celery, carrots and potatoes on top.
Mix salt, sugar, tapioca and juice together and pour over vegetables.
Cover.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours, or if in hurry at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Add peas 30 minutes before removing from oven.

title: honey milk balls
directions: Combine honey and peanut butter; work in dry milk and oats. Shape into balls.
Chill and serve.
Makes 12 balls.

title: treasure chest
directions: Mix together Rice Krispies, nuts and coconut and brown in the oven.
Stir in sugar and butter; put half in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Spoon in the ice cream and put the other half of crumbs on top. Freeze.
This can be made several days ahead.

title: mozzarella ham stromboli
directions: On lightly floured surface, pat dough into a 14 x 12-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over dough to within 1/2-inch of edges.
Top with single layer of ham.
Roll up tightly from a short side; pinch seam to seal.
Place seam side down on an ungreased baking sheet.
Brush top of loaf with butter; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on a wire rack for 5 minutes.
Cut with a serrated knife.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: "russian" chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in casserole dish.
Mix together the soup mix, salad dressing and preserves.
Spread over chicken. Bake, covered, in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: coconut pie
directions: Blend in mixer on low for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie plate.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup of coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: beverly anne's manybean soup
directions: Saute onions or boil with other ingredients.
Add pinto beans with 4 cups water, paprika, celery seed and bay leaves.
Cook for 1 hour.
Wash and add kidney beans and limas.
Add more liquid, if needed.
Cook 1 more hour.
Add peas, dill and salt.
Add liquid to keep soup soupy.
Cook 1 more hour.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Melt the butter in a 9 x 11 x 2-inch baking pan in the oven, taking care that the butter does not start to turn brown.
In a bowl, mix all of the dry ingredients with a wooden spoon.
Pour the melted butter in carefully and mix well.
The crumb mixture will be a little lumpy; it is not supposed to be really smooth. Put half of it back into the pan you melted the butter in.
Spread it out evenly, then put the cherry pie filling all over the top of it.
Finally, put the other half of the crumb mixture on top. Spread it evenly.
Do not stir.
Place the cherry crunch in a 350° oven and bake it for an hour.
Serve it warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Using 1 cup boiling water, dissolve jello.
Wait 5 minutes. Add pineapple and juice; stir well.
Add cranberries, apples, nuts and celery; mix until all is same color.
Refrigerate.
Best if made 24 to 48 hours before using.

title: mincemeat drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift dry ingredients.
Add half to creamed mixture.
Add mincemeat. Stir until blended.
Add nuts and remaining flour mixture; mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased sheet.
Bake at about 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pork casserole
directions: Brown chops.
Place cabbage in casserole, then potatoes. Place onion slices over potatoes.
Spread with soup.
Top with chops.
Cover.
Bake
at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cajun cake
directions: Mix with spoon 1 minute.
Batter will be thick.
Cook at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute diced onions, celery and garlic in margarine until tender. Add the tomato soup, water, Worcestershire sauce and red pepper to taste. Add chicken to mixture. Cook until thick. In chicken broth, cook the spaghetti until tender. Add mixture and mushroom soup. Mix well and place in buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Place in oven until cheese melts. Serve warm.

title: (instant) creamy potato soup
directions: In saucepan, heat to scalding butter, onion, salt, pepper, and milk.
Stir in potato buds; continue cooking until smooth, stirring constantly (soup should be consistency of heavy cream) pour into dishes.
Garnish with paprika and parsley.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble and brown sausage; drain grease.
Butter 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Line with 6 to 8 slices of light bread. Peel crust from bread.
Beat eggs; add salt and pepper to taste. Add milk.
Pour over bread and sausage.
Sprinkle 2 cups of shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Take out about 1 hour before cooking.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour. Serve hot.

title: crock pot stew
directions: Place vegetables in bottom of pot. Season with meat on top. Don't peep or add liquid. Cook on high for 3 hours. Turn to low for 6 hours and serve.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Layer graham crackers on aluminum foil or cookie sheet. Sprinkle with pecans.
Melt butter and sugar in saucepan.
Pour over graham crackers and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool for 1 hour.
Then break in pieces.

title: rigatoni with beef and garden vegetables
directions: Into a 12-inch skillet over medium heat, with garlic press, press garlic.
Add ground beef and onion; cook until beef is well browned, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, salt and pepper; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook beef, onion, green pepper, garlic, salt, and pepper until meat is done. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, and cumin. Simmer 10 minutes. Stir in rice, simmer uncovered for 5 minutes. Remove from heat cover and let stand 5 minutes. Drain grease from meat. Remove tops from peppers and place in boiling water for 4 minutes. Fill peppers with meat. Place rest of the meat in an ungreased 9 x 13 pan. Top with stuffed peppers. Cover and cook on 350° for 1 hour. Heat cheese sauce and cover peppers with cheese sauce.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook and stir meat, onion and green pepper until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Heat through.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Top completely with sliced cheese.
Cover and bake 1 hour.

title: five layer dessert
directions: Mix together; spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Let cool.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat cake mix, water, and almond on low speed of electric mixer.
Fold in coconut.
Line cookie sheets with foil.
Drop spoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 350 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and cut into chunks the chicken breasts.
Mix melted butter and seasoned stuffing.
Mix and heat to boil the cream of chicken, mushroom soup and chicken broth.
Put 1/2 of the stuffing mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Add chicken chunks. Pour soup mixture over this.
Add rest of stuffing mixture.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: easy lo mein
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to box directions.
Drain and set aside to cool.
In a large skillet over high heat add sesame oil and meat.
Once done, remove from pan and set aside.
In same pan, add vegetable oil, crushed red pepper flakes.
Stir-fry the peas, onion, and bean sprouts for 1 minute.
Dump in drained, cooled pasta and toss.
Next add in the meat that was set aside, and fry the mixture until noodles and veggies are combined.
Drizzle with soy sauce and 1 tablespoons of sesame oil.
Dump into large serving bowl.

title: grated potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes. Grate potatoes as you would cabbage (easiest when potatoes are cold). Grease pan. Put potatoes in layers with salt and pepper and butter dots in between layers. Pour 1/2 pint or more (I use 1 pint for 9x12 pan) of Half and Half over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: impossible zucchini tomato pie quiche
directions: Grease a 10-inch quiche dish or pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch). Sprinkle first 4 ingredients in pan.
Blend other 5 ingredients. Pour over and bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: meal-in-one
directions: Cut up okra and squash, salt and roll in corn meal.
Slowly fry in oil and add chopped onion.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients thoroughly.
Sift together and stir in the next 4 ingredients.
Chill dough; roll into balls size of large walnuts.
Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour, crisscross.
Bake until set, but not hard, at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: turkey tenderloin
directions: Blend all ingredients except turkey together in shallow pan. Add turkey, turning to coat; both sides.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for several hours, turning occasionally.
Grill tenderloins over hot coals 8 to 10 minutes per side, depending on thickness.
Tenderloin is done when there is no pink in center of meat.
Do not overcook.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: cheese krispies(club member: amanda speed)
directions: Melt butter and pour over grated cheese; mix other ingredients together with butter. Make into small balls and press with fork. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans in bottom of Bundt pan.
Mix all the remaining ingredients, except syrup, in usual manner in order given in a large mixing bowl.
Reserve 1 cup batter.

title: skillet quick escalloped potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in electric skillet.
Add potatoes and onions. Simmer until tender.
Add cubed ham and soup, diluted with the milk and serve.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a microwave bowl.
Cook on High for 1 minute; take out and stir.
Return to microwave for 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Remove from oven and add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour onto Saran Wrap.
Cool.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Put in wide mouth glass gallon jar in refrigerator.
Stir next day a couple of times.
Ready to eat after third day.
Stays good in refrigerator up to 1 year.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil 1 1/2 cups water and dissolve strawberry jello.
Add cranberry sauce and
undrained pineapple to jello.
Chill for several hours until set.

title: sour cream cucumber salad
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers with salt.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Drain liquid.
Add onions, vinegar and pepper.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot mushroom spread
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Drain. Crumble bacon. Drain off bacon drippings. Reserve 2 tablespoons in pan. Add mushrooms and onion and cook, stirring often, until liquid is evaporated. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce. Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese melts. Stir sour cream and bacon into mushroom mixture. Cook until thoroughly heated, stirring constantly (do not boil). Serve warm with assorted crackers or use as a pate with Beef Wellington.

title: reduced fat chocolate layer pie
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups milk and pudding mix; with mixer, beat 1 minute (mixture will be very thick). Spoon into crust.

title: reduce stress cookies
directions: Dump all ingredients into a large bowl.
Mash it!
Knead it! Pound it!
The longer and harder you mix it, the better it tastes! Roll dough into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: rice pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cooked rice, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, margarine and eggs.
Spread in greased pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Put on pizza sauce, Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Add your favorite toppings too. Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: special k bars
directions: Mix together sugar and syrup.
Heat until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until mixed.
Stir in Rice Krispies and press into buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Melt chips in kettle.
Stir until smooth and spread over bars.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Cook together water and starch until bubbly.
Remove from heat and add Equal and Jell-O.
Stir well.
Let cool until warm to touch, then add strawberries.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix and store dry in a jar.
May want to add more cocoa for more chocolate flavor.
If using straight chocolate, you will need to add some sugar so not so bitter-tasting.

title: calamari rings
directions: Dry squid on paper towels.
Combine dry ingredients and coat squid with flour mixture.
Heat peanut oil to 365°.
Deep fry a few rings at a time until golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot with horseradish, sweet and sour or marinara sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pig in a poke cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake for about 25 minutes at 325°.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a shaker bottle or jar.
Shake well before each use.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy morning casserole(this can be made up and stored in refrigerator overnight.)
directions: Cube buttered bread slices; put half of them in 9 x 12-inch ungreased baking dish.
Add ham or sausage and half of cheese. Mix well the eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour in baking dish.
Add remaining bread cubes and cheese.
Press down.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: eight day pickles
directions: Put ingredients in stone crock.
Add cucumbers (washed) as gathered from garden time to time.
Keeps indefinitely in brine. Can be used when cured 8 days.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix crumbs, butter and sugar.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Slice bananas over crust. Slice ice cream and layer evenly over bananas.
Sprinkle nuts over ice cream.
Press in and freeze.

title: tortilla stew(best served with cornbread)
directions: Place beef, onion, salt, pepper, chili powder and cumin in a large pan.
Cook until meat is brown.
Add the tomato soup, tomatoes, beans, green chilies and corn.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat to simmer and cook for 1 hour.
Just before serving, break tortillas into bite size pieces and mix.

title: bechamel sauce
directions: See recipe for Rich Butter Sauce.
Add cream and grated cheese with Rich Butter Sauce and let cook briefly together to blend thoroughly.

title: jumbo cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook 4 minutes. Add oatmeal and vanilla.
Mix well and drop onto waxed paper.

title: st. croix egg salad
directions: Blend cheese, mayonnaise and spices.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Use 1/2 cup mixture per 1/2 pita bread.

title: skillet mac
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in skillet until browned. Pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients. Heat through and serve.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
