In large bowl combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt (if desired); using fork, mix well. Using pastry blender, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk; using fork, mix just until mixture forms soft dough.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured surface. Knead 6 to 8 times to mix thoroughly.
Roll out dough to 1/2 inch thickness.
With floured cutter, cut out biscuits.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until golden, about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: In colander, drain and rinse beans.
Put beans in a large bowl and add all ingredients, except bacon, and mix well.
Put mixture in casserole dish and top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: cranberry and raisin pie
directions: Line pie plate with crust and use remainder for lattice top. Mix berries and raisins.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add tomato paste, sauce, tomatoes, garlic juice, salt, pepper, basil and oregano.
Cook slowly 30 minutes.
Cook noodles by directions on box.
Arrange in layers noodles, sauce and cheese; repeat.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top layer.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spareribs and kraut
directions: Season ribs with salt and pepper; put in Dutch oven.
Brown well.
Combine remaining ingredients; spoon over ribs.
Simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours, basting several times.
Skim off fat. Add Stuffing Balls.
Cook 15 minutes more.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Diagonally slice each hot dog into 6 pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients into franks.
Cover and chill for 4 hours.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Dissolve baking soda into the sour cream.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening together until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; stir until mixed.
Add baking soda-sour cream mixture; stir well. Add flour, baking powder and salt; stir until well mixed.

title: vera's chicken soup
directions: Mix together 1/3 cup flour and 1/3 cup water for thickening.

title: verla brasher's bazaar bread
directions: Fill a large mixing bowl with hot water from the faucet and let it sit for a minute or two.
Empty, then add 2 cups lukewarm water to the warm bowl.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar and yeast; mix well.
When dissolved, add the sugar (1 cup), Wesson oil, eggs and salt.
Mix well.
Add the flour 1/3 at a time and mix after each addition.
This should make a fairly thick dough.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Grease 3 loaf pans.
Dip the batter by spoonfuls evenly in the pans.
Heat the margarine and spread evenly on top of dough.
Let rise until double.
Bake in 300° oven 30 to 45 minutes or until bread leaves the side of the pans and tests done.
If it browns too fast, cover with foil after the first 15 to 20 minutes.
When done turn out immediately on towel to cool.
Some ovens may take longer to cook.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Heat
oven
to
Mix sugars, margarine, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls
onto
ungreased
cookie sheet about 2-inches apart. Bake until
light brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: microwave baked custard
directions: Microwave
the	milk
in
a 2 cup measure on High until tiny bubbles
appear around edges of cup, 2 to 3 1/2 minutes. Mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla in a 1 quart bowl.	Blend in milk.	Divide into 4 to 6 ounce baking cups.
Sprinkle nutmeg on
top.
Arrange cups in ring around outer edge of carousel. Microwave on Medium-high (70%) until center resembles soft set gelatin,	4
to 7 minutes.	Center will become firm as custard cools.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: lemon walnut cake(makes approximately 16 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10 cup fluted tube pan.
In a large bowl, cream sugar and margarine.
Stir in eggs. Add lemon juice, lemon peel and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix. Grease pans; fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 large loaves or 4 little loaves.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: In
skillet,
over
medium
heat, brown meat and onions until done.
Pour off drippings.	Stir in corn, tomato sauce, rice, steak sauce and pepper.
Set aside.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as
per package.
Add all other ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and milk in a saucepan; bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chips until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch square or 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Lightly steam or parboil broccoli and drain.
Saute onion in butter until soft, then toss with broccoli.
Line pastry shell with Swiss cheese.
Arrange broccoli over cheese.
Beat half and half with eggs and seasonings.
Pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour and baking soda. Set aside.
In a large bowl, cream the butter, sugars and vanilla extract.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in morsels and nuts. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Pour into casserole dish. Take 1 stack of Ritz crackers and break and mix with 1/4 cup butter. Put on top and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: mrs. thornton's strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, beat for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into sprayed 9 x 12-inch pan or 2 or 3 round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 37 minutes for 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: sausage in tomato and sage
directions: Saute sausage in 1/2 tablespoon oil.
After turning, add juice and simmer 5 minutes.
Chop vegetables and saute in 1 1/2 tablespoons oil, adding sage, basil and oregano.
Add tomatoes, cream and red wine; simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add sausage to sauce. Serve over pasta (rotini).

title: apple crumble
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch) or rectangular baking dish (10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch).
Arrange apples in dish.
Mix baking mix, sugar and egg until crumbly; sprinkle over apples.
Drizzle margarine over top; sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake until topping is golden brown and apples are tender, 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Make your favorite meat loaf and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread celery soup or chicken soup over meat loaf.
Top with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix well and bake in one crust 1/2 to 3/4 hour slowly.
When done, cover with the beaten whites and brown.

title: pirate's pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add to separated chunks of tuna.
Add mushrooms and parsley.
Place mix in bottom of well-greased 9-inch pie tin.
Top with tomato slices and 3 of cheese slices.
Prepare mashed potato mix, using 1/2 cup less liquid than package directions call for.
Spoon potatoes over cheese.
Cut remaining cheese slice in narrow strips and put on pie in a wagon wheel spoke design.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until potatoes are lightly browned and cheese melts.
Cut into wedges and serve hot. Garnish with parsley and/or paprika.
Serves 4.

title: easy spinach-asparagus quiche
directions: While the spinach is cooking, prepare the asparagus by removing the tough lower parts.
Cut the asparagus into pieces the length of the tip of your thumb to the first knuckle.
Place in the bottom of the pie crust with the spinach.
Spread the cheese evenly over the spinach and asparagus.
Mix the milk, eggs, butter and salt together and pour over the asparagus, spinach and cheese.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes or until the top is evenly browned.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip.
Fold in Cool Whip. Freeze and serve.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat.
Cook frozen broccoli as directed and drain.
Heat cream of mushroom soup.
Melt Velveeta cheese.
Cook Minute rice as directed.
Mix all ingredients together in a large baking dish and bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until hot all through.
Serves about 10 to 12.

title: basic marinara sauce(heart healthy)
directions: In a skillet, simmer garlic and onion in the olive oil until onions are translucent and garlic is lightly browned. Transfer the onion, garlic and olive oil to a large Dutch oven or kettle. Add the pureed tomatoes, crushed tomatoes and tomato paste and stir together, mixing with the olive oil, onions and garlic. Begin to simmer the sauce on as low a heat as possible, stirring frequently to prevent burning. After simmering for about 10 minutes, add the wine and herbs, stirring to disperse throughout the sauce. Simmer the sauce for at least 2 hours, stirring frequently to prevent sauce on the bottom of the kettle from burning. Add salt and pepper to taste. Additional amounts of herbs or wine can be added to taste as well. The sauce is best when simmered slowly up to 4 hours to allow the full flavor of all the ingredients to blend. Serves 8.

title: german red cabbage
directions: In a pan over medium heat, saute bacon until translucent. Add onion, sliced cabbage and apples.
Saute, uncovered, until cabbage begins to collapse.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Sift together three times.
Add nuts to dry ingredients and mix well. Set aside.

title: syrup cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs, syrup, milk, flour, soda and spices.
Bake in large pan at 350°.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Cool and cut into small pieces.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Crumble crackers and spread over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with poppy seed and pour melted margarine on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Cook broccoli as directed.
Saute onion in butter. Mix cream of mushroom soup with Cheez Whiz.
Add rice, onion, broccoli (drained) and 1 cup onion rings.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover, sprinkle 1/4 cup onion rings on top and bake 5 more minutes.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix and make a smooth dough.
Shape into small balls and roll very thin.
Fry on ungreased grill.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel onions and tomatoes.
Chop all vegetables and mix with grated cheese, bacon, salt and pepper. Place in 2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs (or mix them in).
Dot with butter.
Bake 20 minutes covered and 10 minutes uncovered.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Add beaten eggs to brown sugar, molasses and oil.
Combine dry ingredients and sift.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in boiling water. Bake in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes or until springy to the touch.

title: veggie-tofu scramble
directions: Saute vegetables in oil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Set aside. Combine tofu with spices.
Add to vegetables.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Garnish with parsley or scallions, and serve.

title: mike's chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Stir in oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake in moderate oven at 375° for about 12 minutes.
Yields 6 1/2 dozen.

title: banana split pie(serves 8)
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with melted margarine.
Press in bottom and sides of pie pan.
Set aside to cool.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add alternately with milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold whites into cake mixture with vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 10 cup tube pan and bake 1 1/2 hours or until cake pulls away from edges of pan and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 25 minutes in pan, then turn out onto rack.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Cover bottom of large casserole dish (or two smaller ones) with chicken.
Mix together soups, milk and water.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing mix with eggs (beaten), broth and butter (margarine).
Have stuffing mix soft and spoon on top of the chicken and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: "sugar free" pudding squares
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers. Cover with 1/2 of the pudding.
Cover again with crackers and pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Let stand in refrigerator several hours.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix together melted margarine, Worcestershire sauce, prepared mustard and onion.
Split rolls in half.
Use a pastry brush to pat mixture on both sides of rolls.
Place 2 slices of ham and 1 slice of cheese on each roll.
After putting rolls together, brush additional mixture thinly on top of each roll.
Cover with foil. Heat in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Great for cover-dish dinners.

title: sweet cinnamon rice
directions: Cover rice with water good.
Put on low flame with lid (watch it so it doesn't boil over).
After the water cooks down a lot, turn fire out.
Leave lid a little ajar.
When ready to fix, add milk, butter, salt, vanilla and sugar.
Mix in bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar/cinnamon.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown beef slowly in oil.
Add onion, garlic, green peppers, celery and broth.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Thicken with cornstarch blended with water and soy sauce.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: broccoli salad #2
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crisp, crumbled bacon on top.

title: chicken continental
directions: Roll chicken in seasoned flour.
Saute in butter until brown. Remove chicken and pour off grease.
Combine soup, onion and seasonings in skillet.
Gradually stir in water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Pour rice in shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in all but 2/3 cup soup mixture.
Top with chicken.
Pour reserved soup mix over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken; take off bones.
Place in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bring to boil soup and vegetables; pour over chicken.
Mix margarine, flour, buttermilk, salt and pepper; spoon the mixture over all.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes in 425° oven, until brown.

title: spiced apple pie filling for canning
directions: Wash, core, peel and slice apples.
Mix sugar, spices, tapioca and water.
Stir over heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add apples and bring to a boil over moderate heat.
Lower heat; cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until apples are tender.
Add lemon juice.
If liquid is thick, thin with boiling water to consistency of honey.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt cheese and oleo; remove from heat.
Add sugar, cocoa, vanilla and nuts; beat well.
Then spread into buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Place marshmallows in large pot and melt (stirring constantly) slow.
Add fruit and nuts to crackers. Pour marshmallows over mixture and mix well.
Add a little evaporated milk if more moisture is needed.
Spoon into a buttered loaf pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from pan and wrap in foil.
Keeps 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: 100 year old pie crust
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients with a fork or pastry blender.
Beat together egg, vinegar, water and extract and add to flour mixture. Mix well and shape into pie crusts.
Use right away or freeze. If dough dries while rolling out, add a few drops of water and mold together dry, broken places.

title: something good little cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place cupcake baking papers in muffin tins.
Add 1 vanilla wafer, flat side down, to each paper.

title: banana loaf
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Add beaten egg. Combine soda, milk and banana.
Add to shortening mixture. Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture.

title: nippy nuts
directions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat; stir in spices.
Add almonds and cook 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add pecans, stirring until coated.
Spread in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool.
Yields 4 cups.

title: sauteed sauerkraut
directions: Put sauerkraut in a colander; rinse thoroughly under cold water.
Drain well; squeeze dry and set aside on paper towels. Fry bacon until crisp; set aside.
Discard all but 3 to 4 tablespoons fat from skillet.
Add onion; cook until soft, 3 minutes.
Add sauerkraut; cook, stirring often, until hot. Combine brown sugar, vinegar, caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Add to skillet and simmer gently 15 minutes.
Crumble bacon and fold in.
Remove from heat and serve hot.

title: pickles
directions: In a large 1/2 gallon container, alternate sliced cucumbers and onions.
Dissolve sugar and salt in vinegar; pour over pickles.

title: tuna noodle bake
directions: Stir the soup, milk and minced onion together.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Top with croutons or bread crumbs if desired.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain excess fat.
Add spaghetti sauce, water, and salt.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
In a 9 x 13 inch casserole or lasagne pan, layer 1/3 sauce, 1/2 uncooked lasagne pieces, 1 c. cottage cheese, 1/3 mozzarella cheese, 1/3 American cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce and remaining mozzarella, american, and parmesan cheeses.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350 degrees for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove foil, and let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: sally's creamy fruit salad
directions: In 2-quart bowl, combine fruit and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: kraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and store in refrigerator. Serves 12.

title: french dressing
directions: Put ingredients in jar and shake well.
Make ahead to season.

title: noodle cookies
directions: Put butterscotch bits in double boiler to melt.
Dump in noodles and peanuts.
Mix and put on wax paper in clumps. Refrigerate 1/2 hour.

title: creamy butter frosting
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat butter until light and fluffy. Gradually add about half of the powdered sugar; beat well.
Beat in vanilla and egg.
Gradually beat in remaining powdered sugar. Beat in some milk, if necessary, to make frosting of spreading consistency.
Cover; store in refrigerator.

title: blitzes
directions: Put eggs in bowl; stir in flour and sugar until mixed.
Slowly add milk; melt butter and add, then salt.
Over a low gas flame, pour batter to cover bottom of frying pan.
Fry until light color on both sides.
Fill with jelly, sugar or fruit.
Roll up and eat. Makes 5 to 6 large "Blitzes".

title: blt dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight. Place on bed of lettuce if desired. Serve with toast.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients into ungreased pie pan.
Combine oil and milk; whip until cloudy.
Pour over flour mixture; mix with fork until blended.
Pat into shape with hands.
Prick and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
You are now ready to pour your favorite filling into the cooked crust.

title: quick apple dessert
directions: Place apples in buttered 11 x 13-inch or similar baking dish. Sprinkle dry jello over apples.
Combine flour and sugar in small bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan log
directions: Mix together. Form into log. Refrigerate. Slices well after refrigerated about 12 hours.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Beat together sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks.
Add juice and rind of lemon, flour and milk.
Mix well.
Add egg whites.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: creamed pheasant
directions: Parboil pheasant.
Combine onion, mushrooms and celery with milk.
Mix in soups and desired chunks of pheasant.
Heat over low heat.
Serve over drop (Bisquick) biscuits.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Spread mix on both sides of roll. Place ham and cheese on rolls.
Wrap in foil.
Heat 10 minutes at 400°.
Can make ahead and refrigerate.
If so, heat 15 minutes. Can freeze and then thaw in refrigerator.
Serves 12.

title: easy oven lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add water, sauce and salt.
Bring to boil. In 2-quart dish, layer hot sauce, uncooked lasagna, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce. Garnish with Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting into squares.
Serves 6.

title: deviled egg salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatine on water to soften.
Dissolve over low heat. Add salt, lemon juice, Worcestershire and pepper; let cool.
Stir in mayo and fold in remaining ingredients.
This fills a 3-cup mold.
I double recipe.
Enjoy.

title: low-fat barbecued chicken
directions: Combine catsup, sugar and vinegar in skillet.
Simmer over low heat for 2 minutes.
Add chicken breasts.
Cover skillet with lid. Turn chicken once or twice while cooking.
Add a little water while cooking if needed.
Simmer for 40 minutes.
Chicken legs and thighs can also be used.
Just remove the skin first.

title: candied kielbasi
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not cover.

title: cheesy egg casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir into sauce; set aside.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a skillet; add onion, mushrooms, parsley and pimiento.
Saute until tender.
Stir mushroom mixture, celery salt and sherry into cheese sauce.
Pour into a greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Grate egg yolks; sprinkle over casserole.
Serve over toast points.
Makes 8 servings.
Good for brunch.

title: baked cod supreme
directions: Place cod fillets in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Slice onion and spread evenly on top of fillets.
Shake on pepper.
Dot with margarine; sprinkle with dill weed and pour milk into pan.
Bake, covered, at 450° for 10 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking 5 minutes more until flaky.

title: carol's dirt cake
directions: You will need one 8-inch clay flower pot lined with foil.

title: english peas in sauce
directions: Cook bacon and onion in skillet until done.
Add flour, whipping cream, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Drain peas and add to sauce and cook for a few minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into Bundt pan or angel food cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let cake cool completely before dumping.

title: easy lemon cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: quick mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain fat. Add refried beans and stir until both are a smooth mixture. Grease bottom and sides of a 2 1/2-quart microwave casserole dish.

title: sauce for meat loaf
directions: Mix tomato sauce, sugar and vinegar in bowl; let stand.
Split meat loaf in center.
Pour half of sauce in meat loaf and remaining sauce in center over loaf.

title: sweet frosting
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar, flour and milk; add vanilla and egg whites. Mix well and frost your cake after it's cool.

title: barbecue sauce supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour over chicken, ribs or beef and marinate overnight.
Can be baked in oven or on grill, covered with aluminum foil.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or lightly browned.
Stir once while baking.

title: easy cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream together magarine and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until well blended.
In a medium bowl, combine next five ingredients; add to creamed mixture. Stir to combine thoroughly.
Stir in apples and walnuts; spoon into greased 10-inch tube pan.

title: butterscotch coffee cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Spread nuts on bottom.
Place dry pudding mix.
Melt butter, add sugar and cinnamon and pour over rolls. Cover with towel and leave overnight.
Do not refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert onto plate and pinch off or slice.

title: pasta fagiola(bean soup with pasta)
directions: Sort and wash beans; place beans in a large Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans and let soak 12 to 24 hours. Drain beans and return to Dutch oven.
Add 4 cups water and next 11 ingredients; stir well.
Bring to boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour and 35 minutes or until beans are tender.
Remove and discard bay leaf.
Add macaroni and cook 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Ladle soup into individual soup bowls. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Yield:
9 cups.

title: polish balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except powdered sugar, mixing well. Form into 1-inch balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool slightly.
Roll each in powdered sugar.
Yields approximately 4 dozen.

title: raspberry swirl cream cheese
directions: Using a food processor or electric mixer, combine cream cheese, yogurt and sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Alternately spoon cream cheese mixture and raspberry preserves into a small serving bowl.
Gently stir in circular motion to form swirls; do not mix completely.
Serve immediately or store covered in refrigerator up to 5 days.
(If mixture separates during storage, stir to blend.)

title: cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients into a batter.
Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with fruit.
Pour batter over fruit.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water; pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green beans supreme
directions: In skillet, cook onion in butter slightly, about 1 minute. Blend in flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once and cook until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream.
Add beans.
Spread one third of the bean mixture into a disposable casserole pan.
Sprinkle one half of the Swiss cheese over the beans; repeat layers, ending with the beans.

title: scapidella(italian stew)
directions: Toss beef and chicken in flour; shake off excess flour.
Brown beef and chicken in oil; set aside.
Return beef to pot.
Add tomatoes, water, 1/2 cup of wine, salt and Worcestershire.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Add chicken parts; simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Cool. Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, skim off fat.
Add 1/2 cup wine; add more water if needed.
Simmer for 10 minutes, or until hot.
Serve over pasta or rice.

title: each peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: In a large saucepan, melt peanut butter chips in 1 cup of condensed milk and 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir.
Remove from heat and spread onto waxed paper-lined 11 x 7-inch pan.
In a small saucepan melt chocolate morsels, the remaining condensed milk, 2 tablespoons butter and evaporated milk.
Spread chocolate on top of peanut butter mixture.
Chill for 2 hours in refrigerator or about 1/2 hour in freezer.
Cut into pieces and serve.

title: party dinner ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix butter, poppy seed, onions and mustard.
Slice dinner rolls.
Remove tops of rolls.
Spread butter mixture on both sides (top and bottom) of rolls.
Place cheese and ham on bottom layer of rolls.
Top with top layer of rolls.
If there is any of the butter mixture left in bowl, brush on top of rolls.
Heat at 325° until cheese melts.
Slice section of rolls while warm.

title: grannie's biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Work shortening together with flour with hands.
When shortening is worked in, mix in enough buttermilk to form a soft dough.
Roll out into biscuits and place into greased pan.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: baked virginia ham
directions: Scrub ham with brush and clean well.
Soak ham in water more than 12 hours, skin side up so salt will drop to bottom, being sure to use enough to cover ham well.
Drain water off; then cover with fresh water and simmer twenty minutes per pound, turning ham during cooking.
Let cool in same water.
Skin ham and rub over with dry mustard and brown sugar, and thin layer of toasted bread crumbs.
Add paprika and whole cloves every square inch.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes, basting every 5 minutes with 1 quart of ginger ale.

title: 10 minute chicken
directions: Melt margarine in frypan.
Cut chicken in small bite size pieces.
Over medium heat, add chicken, garlic, salt and pepper. Cook until golden.
Prepare rice while chicken is cooking.
Mix the soup and milk in a bowl; heat in microwave for 2 minutes.
Place as much rice as desired on plate.
Add 6 to 10 pieces of chicken on top of rice.
Pour cream of mushroom sauce over top.
This whole process takes 10 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper; drain.
Add spices and tomato products; set aside.
Combine cottage cheese and Parmesan; set aside.
Grate remaining cheeses, set aside.
Half cook the lasagna noodles.
In an oblong casserole dish, put a layer of half the noodles.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Spread all the cottage cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Layer with remaining noodles and sprinkle with cheese.
Spread tomato mixture and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: waldorf astoria cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add vanilla, vinegar and food coloring.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with buttermilk. Pour batter in 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Form into balls; roll in powdered sugar and cover, then put in refrigerator.

title: seafood dip
directions: Blend first six ingredients.
Spread in pie pan.
Top with walnuts.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Pour can cherries in square cake pan.
Spread on bottom of pan. Then pour crushed pineapple on top of cherries and spread. Pour cake mix on top of pineapple.
Then melt 2 sticks of Promise margarine and pour over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350°.
Bake until it gets brown on top.

title: cantaloupe frost
directions: Freeze melon cubes until firm.
In a blender container, combine the frozen melon cubes, milk and ginger.
Cover; blend until slushy.
With blender running, add sherbet, a spoonful at a time, through hole in lid, blending until thoroughly combined.
Stop machine to scrape down sides as necessary.
Serve immediately in chilled glasses.
Garnish with orange peel curls, if desired. Makes 6 (8-ounce) servings.

title: hot chicken salad and rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, then rinse with cold water.
Combine all ingredients except cheese and mix well. Spoon into a greased ovenproof casserole.
Top with grated cheese and refrigerate.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: potato nachos
directions: In microwave-safe pie plate or shallow baking dish, arrange potatoes in single layer.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Brush with half of the taco sauce.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap.
Cook on High 4 to 5 minutes or until potatoes are tender, rotating dish once.

title: blender salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; process well.
Yields about 2 cups.

title: collette's eggs
directions: Melt butter in nonstick frying pan.
Add eggs.
Cook eggs slowly until you start to see the yolk change.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, at least 1/8-inch thick.
Slowly add vinegar, one teaspoon at a time,
to the outer edge of the pan.
This will flash cook the eggs.
Serve with bread and preserves.

title: sally lunn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased muffin pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook in crock-pot on High for 5 hours (first 2 1/2 hours with lid on, last 2 1/2 hours with lid off).
Fill hot jars and seal. You may cook for a longer period of time, if desired.

title: pizza dough
directions: Use ingredients in order given.
Mix and knead with your hands until you have a smooth dough.
Let rise until it has doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Divide in half to make 2 (14-inch) round pizzas or 1 large.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Put favorite toppings on and bake about 12 to 15 minutes at 500°.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine, add sugar and cocoa; stir well.
Add eggs and stir well, do not beat.
Add milk and vanilla; stir well.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: mexican chicken
directions: In 2-quart casserole sprayed with Pam, place rice on bottom. Mix 1 package taco seasoning mix and water.
Pour over rice.
Layer onions, then chicken.
Sprinkle second package of taco mix on top. Microwave on High for 35 minutes in covered dish.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer 2 hours.
Age at least one month in refrigerator or cool dark place.
Will keep several months.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter with 2 cups sugar until light and fluffy.
Add beaten egg yolks, sift flour and baking powder together.
Add vanilla to milk.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Fold in 4 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Divide into 3 greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked bananas
directions: Cut bananas in chunks; place in a baking dish.
Coat with mixture of butter, lemon juice and honey.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon which have been mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until pinkish color.
Be careful not to burn.

title: main dish for six
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cook macaroni until soft; drain.
Mix ham and onion together.
Mix macaroni with ham and onion.
Pour soup over the top of macaroni and ham.
Sprinkle top with celery salt.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sausage and cheese tidbits(appetizer "easy")
directions: Mix and form into small balls.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Makes 60 to 65 balls.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Bake as needed.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Blend shortening and margarine together in large mixer bowl on medium high speed.

Add sugar gradually and beat until fluffy. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour and soda together; add alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Add 1 2/3 cups coconut to cake batter.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into batter.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30
minutes.
Cool.
Frost cake with filling.
(This is good as a sheet cake.)

title: oatmeal toll house cookies
directions: Combine in the usual manner (I usually mix this heavy dough with my hands).
Cream sugars and shortening together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together dry ingredients (flour, salt, soda and baking powder).
Slowly add flour mixture to sugars, etc.
Mix until well blended (dough will be sticky).
Add chocolate chips and oatmeal.

title: blueberry armagnac syrup(for ice cream)
directions: Sort berries; rinse, drain and dry on paper towels.
Divide berries between 3 hot, clean pint jars, shaking as you go to lightly pack.
Leave 1/2-inch head room.
Pour 2 to 3 tablespoons Armagnac or cognac into each jar.
Boil water and sugar in large saucepan, uncovered, for 3 minutes.
Fill jars with this syrup, leaving 1/2-inch headroom.
Seal jars according to directions. Process in boiling water bath 15 minutes.
Cool and label.

title: homemade cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients and pour into greased pan.
Bake until brown.

title: jello salad(diabetic)
directions: Heat pineapple and jello together.
Let come to bubble; boil. Add buttermilk and fold in remaining ingredients.
Make big Pyrex dish full.
